BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Iredell County Public Library Commemorates 250 Years of Freedom
  with Year-Long Exhibit Series\n\nThe Iredell County Public Library will ho
 st a series of four local history exhibits throughout 2026 as part of Ameri
 ca 250\, the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Indepen
 dence. The inaugural exhibit\, Visions of Freedom\, will open to the public
  on January 12 on the Main floor of the Statesville branch library.\n\nVisi
 ons of Freedom will focus on highlighting local landmarks\, Revolutionary e
 ra residents\, and important social movements that not only shaped the nati
 on\, but the Iredell County community. This free exhibit will offer a blend
  of information\, images\, and engaging interactive activities designed to 
 appeal to visitors of all ages.\n\nFor more details about the exhibit serie
 s and upcoming local history events\, please visit our website at https://i
 redell.lib.nc.us or contact Shellie Taylor at michelle.taylor@iredellcounty
 nc.gov\n\nStatesville Library Hours: M-Th 8am-8pm\, F & Sat 9am-6pm
DTEND:20260310T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260309T120000Z
GEO:35.787463;-80.88791
LOCATION:Iredell County Public Library\, Main level
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Visions of Freedom\, Exhibit #1 (Iredell County Public Library: Mai
 n Branch-Statesville)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764560081921
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/visions-of-freedom-exhibit-1-iredell-c
 ounty-public-library-main-branch-statesville
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Do you love watching and/or listening to birds? Have you always
  wanted to pick up birdwatching as a hobby and wanted a group to birdwatch 
 and learn with? Join a Ranger to birdwatch along the trails. Don’t forget y
 our binoculars!\n\nAll children must be accompanied by an adult. Please be 
 sure to dress appropriately for the weather\, wear hiking shoes\, bring wat
 er and binoculars!\n\nSpaces are limited\, and registration is required. To
  sign up\, call (984) 250-1370 or email eno.river@ncparks.gov. Include the 
 number of guests in your party and a phone number where you can be reached 
 if the event is changed or canceled.
DTEND:20260309T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260309T123000Z
GEO:36.078519;-79.005129
LOCATION:Eno River State Park - Fews Ford Access\, Fews Ford Picnic Shelter
  (End of the Road)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Early Birds
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52152499567560
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/early-birds
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive audiovisual experience as we illuminat
 e Harriet Jacobs\, a fugitive North Carolina enslaved person who hid in a t
 iny attic garret for seven years. While hiding she planned her escape\, fle
 d to the North\, and eventually became a key figure in the abolitionist mov
 ement.\n\nIn celebration of Black History Month\, we invite you to explore 
 a to-scale recreation of Harriet’s attic space and listen to readings from 
 her book\, Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl\, which was published in 1
 861.
DTEND:20260310T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260309T130000Z
GEO:39.168209;-86.519998
LOCATION:Malloy/Jordan East Winston Heritage Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Harriet Jacobs in the Attic
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52092289841989
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:In commemoration of America's 250th\, the Bellamy Mansion Museu
 m is hosting an art exhibition by local artist James C. Horton\, which incl
 udes over 40 original paintings and drawings that highlight historic scenes
  and places from around the region and country that help tell America's sto
 ry. Visitors can view the exhibit free of charge any time the museum is ope
 n (M-Sun. 10 am-4 pm). Please stop by the Carriage ​House Visitor Center to
  gain admission. Art is available for purchase and an Artist's Reception wi
 ll be held on February 27th (6-8pm). Visit bellamymansion.org/exhibits for 
 more information or email info@bellamymansion.org if you have questions.
DTEND:20260310T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260309T140000Z
GEO:34.236116;-77.942949
LOCATION:Bellamy Mansion Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Legends & Landmarks: Paintings and Drawings by James C. Horton
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51861474301240
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/legends-landmarks-paintings-and-drawin
 gs-by-james-c-horton
END:VEVENT
