BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Spring is on the way and so are the salamanders! Join a Ranger 
 on a 1.6-mile round-trip hike to the Eno Quarry to learn about the Spotted 
 Salamander and other amphibians that live around the Eno River.\n\nAll chil
 dren must be accompanied by an adult. Please be sure to dress appropriately
  for the weather\, wear shoes that can get muddy\, and bring water!\n\nSpac
 es are limited\, and registration is required. To sign up\, call (984) 250-
 1370 or email eno.river@ncparks.gov. Include the number of guests in your p
 arty and a phone number where you can be reached if the event is changed or
  canceled.
DTEND:20260311T163000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260311T140000Z
GEO:36.039761;-78.990417
LOCATION:Eno River State Park - Cabelands Access\, Parking Lot
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Salamander Spring
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52152543817753
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/salamander-spring-5828
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation
DESCRIPTION:Ready for some frog squats? This full body workout mimicking an
 imal movements can help. The first 5-10 minutes will focus on stretching an
 d warming up our muscle groups. This will be followed by 10 minutes of body
  movement practice leading into a 20-minute circuit of those learned moveme
 nts\, known as an AMRAP (as many rounds/reps as possible). We’ll end with a
  10-minute cool down. This will be physically challenging\, but movements c
 an be modified. Meet in the open lawn near the Visitor’s Center. Program is
  weather dependen
DTEND:20260311T150000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260311T140000Z
GEO:34.670531;-77.143056
LOCATION:Hammocks Beach State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Wilderness Workout
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52198658802441
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/wilderness-workout-8728
