BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive audiovisual experience as we illuminat
 e Harriet Jacobs\, a fugitive North Carolina enslaved person who hid in a t
 iny attic garret for seven years. While hiding she planned her escape\, fle
 d to the North\, and eventually became a key figure in the abolitionist mov
 ement.\n\nIn celebration of Black History Month\, we invite you to explore 
 a to-scale recreation of Harriet’s attic space and listen to readings from 
 her book\, Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl\, which was published in 1
 861.
DTEND:20260313T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260312T130000Z
GEO:39.168209;-86.519998
LOCATION:Malloy/Jordan East Winston Heritage Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Harriet Jacobs in the Attic
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52092289844040
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Homeschool & Education Days
DESCRIPTION:Join us for all of our homeschool day programs for the 2025-202
 6 school year! After everyone registers\, our team will put each student in
  a group for the field trip. Make sure you include the Co-op or group you w
 ould like to be with on the registration form. You can register for all the
  homeschool day programs now\, or you can register each month.\n\nDates and
  Themes:\n\nOctober 8- Espionage\nNovember 5- NC Ironclads and Civil War We
 apons\nDecember 17- Victorian Christmas\nJanuary 8- Environmental Education
 \nFebruary 12- NC History\nMarch 12- Women's History\nApril 16- NC Governme
 nt\n\nFor each of these programs\, staff from other NC Historic Sites\, oth
 er State of NC agencies\, volunteers\, and nonprofit organizations will ass
 ist in creating engaging experiences for your homeschool student(s). We aim
  to include as many hands-on activities as possible. Most of our stations w
 ill last around twelve minutes\, and families will have a chance to rotate 
 through several stations. Some months\, we will also feature a guest speake
 r\, with additional details sent out before the program.\n\nThe cost is $2.
 00 plus tax per student. Beginning in October\, adult admission will be fre
 e\, but everyone will still need to register. Ages 3 and under are free.\n\
 nRegistration link: https://tinyurl.com/y49amdu7\n\nRegistration will close
  on the Monday before the event date\, so we can organize groups and send o
 ut the list. We will reopen registration after each homeschool day program 
 is finished.\n\nIf you have any questions\, please email Rachel at rachel.k
 ennedy@dncr.nc.gov.
DTEND:20260312T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260312T140000Z
GEO:35.260403;-77.581573
LOCATION:CSS Neuse Civil War Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:CSS Neuse Museum Homeschool Day 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50922155539459
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/css-neuse-museum-homeschool-day-6030
END:VEVENT
