BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join The Moravian Archives for a lecture on the influence of Mo
 ravian mapmaking on the Race to the Dan\, the Battle of Guildford Courthous
 e\, and more.\n\nJoin Archivist Sabrina Garity for a lecture about the end 
 of the Revolutionary War\, map making\, Moravian involvement\, and more. Th
 is lecture will focus on the influence of accurate maps of the waterways in
  North Carolina on the Race to the Dan\, a campaign in which Lord Cornwalli
 s pursued Nathaniel Greene across the Carolinas in early 1781. The connecti
 on between Moravians with both British and American forces will be discusse
 d\, as well as the Battle of Guildford Courthouse. Following the lecture\, 
 a showcase of Archival records from the collection will be highlighted.
DTEND:20260313T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030915Z
DTSTART:20260313T170000Z
GEO:36.089492;-80.241052
LOCATION:The Archie K. Davis Center \, Recital Hall
SEQUENCE:0
