BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Panels & Book Discussions
DESCRIPTION:The SLNC Government and Heritage Library invites you to join us
  for a webinar featuring author Sally M. Walker\, who will discuss Within O
 ur Power: The Story of the Edenton Ladies' Tea Party.\nThis illustrated chi
 ldren’s book tells the story of 51 women in Edenton\, North Carolina\, who 
 took a political stand by signing a resolution to boycott British tea and g
 oods in 1774. In this webinar\, Walker will explore the historical context 
 of the Edenton Tea Party\, the lives and motivations of the women involved\
 , and the lasting legacy of their actions. A live Q&A session will follow t
 he talk\, giving attendees the opportunity to engage directly with the auth
 or.
DTEND:20260318T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260318T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Within Our Power: The Story of the Edenton Ladies' Tea Party!
