BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Iredell County Public Library Commemorates 250 Years of Freedom
  with Year-Long Exhibit Series\n\nThe Iredell County Public Library will ho
 st a series of four local history exhibits throughout 2026 as part of Ameri
 ca 250\, the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Indepen
 dence. The inaugural exhibit\, Visions of Freedom\, will open to the public
  on January 12 on the Main floor of the Statesville branch library.\n\nVisi
 ons of Freedom will focus on highlighting local landmarks\, Revolutionary e
 ra residents\, and important social movements that not only shaped the nati
 on\, but the Iredell County community. This free exhibit will offer a blend
  of information\, images\, and engaging interactive activities designed to 
 appeal to visitors of all ages.\n\nFor more details about the exhibit serie
 s and upcoming local history events\, please visit our website at https://i
 redell.lib.nc.us or contact Shellie Taylor at michelle.taylor@iredellcounty
 nc.gov\n\nStatesville Library Hours: M-Th 8am-8pm\, F & Sat 9am-6pm
DTEND:20260320T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260319T120000Z
GEO:35.787463;-80.88791
LOCATION:Iredell County Public Library\, Main level
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Visions of Freedom\, Exhibit #1 (Iredell County Public Library: Mai
 n Branch-Statesville)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764560095243
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/visions-of-freedom-exhibit-1-iredell-c
 ounty-public-library-main-branch-statesville
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions,Organizational,Celebrations & Comme
 morations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries,Open Houses
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to explore the history of Davie County as the S
 emiquincentennial draws closer. There will be historical artifacts on displ
 ay representing the county's history. This includes a portrait of Continent
 al Army Colonel William R. Davie\, the county's namesake. There's also a lo
 t of information on Daniel Boone\, who lived in Davie County for seven year
 s. His parents are buried in Mocksville's Joppa Cemetery. Feel free to brow
 se around the room and examine historical records and documents\, including
  a list of those who served during the American Revolution. \n\nThese artif
 acts and documents are located inside the Martin-Wall History Room within t
 he Davie County Public Library in Mocksville. This room acts as the Davie C
 ounty history museum. Paying a visit will allow you to explore the county's
  long and proud history while gaining a better understanding of the Semiqui
 ncentennial's significance. These artifacts will be on display from Monday\
 , March 16\, until at least Sunday\, July 6.
DTEND:20260319T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260319T130000Z
GEO:35.897815;-80.5597
LOCATION:Davie County Public Library\, Martin-Wall History Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:History on Display
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52372920351524
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/history-on-display
END:VEVENT
