BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Honoring America’s Forgotten Patriots at the USS North Carolina
 \n\nAs part of the nationwide commemoration of America’s 250th anniversary\
 , the Stamp Defiance Chapter\, NSDAR\, invites the public to the Dedication
  of the Daughters of the American Revolution America 250 Plaque honoring Am
 erica’s Forgotten Patriots of the American Revolution.\n\nThe dedication wi
 ll take place on March 20\, 2026\, at 10:00 a.m. at Battleship Park\, home 
 of the USS North Carolina\, in Wilmington\, North Carolina. Remarks will be
  provided by Dr. Jay Martin\, Director of the USS North Carolina\, along wi
 th additional commentary recognizing the service and sacrifice of Forgotten
  Patriots whose contributions helped secure American independence.\n\nThe S
 ons of the American Revolution Color Guard will present the Colors. The Eug
 ene Ashley High School NJROTC will serve as Honor Guard and lead the Pledge
  of Allegiance\, and the Tryon Palace Fife and Drum Corps will perform trad
 itional 18th-century military tunes. A reception will follow the dedication
  ceremony.\n\nThe National Society Daughters of the American Revolution is 
 proud to be the first heritage society to formally partner with America250\
 , the nationwide initiative led by the U.S. Semiquincentennial Commission. 
 This partnership supports DAR’s mission to honor Revolutionary War Patriots
 \, promote education\, engage youth\, and highlight the diverse individuals
  who shaped our nation’s founding
DTEND:20260320T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260320T140000Z
GEO:34.236158;-77.953643
LOCATION: Battleship North Carolina\, Battleship Park and Ward Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Stamp Defiance Chapter NSDAR America 250 Plaque Dedication
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51993822019673
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/stamp-defiance-chapter-nsdar-america-2
 50-plaque-dedication
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260320T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260320T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082914999
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
