DESCRIPTION:Visit Horne Creek Farm on Saturday\, March 21st\, to purchase s
 ome heirloom apple trees grafted from our orchard for planting around the h
 ome or farm. We will have numerous varieties to choose from\, and you are s
 ure to find one that works for you. Jason Bowen\, the site’s horticulturist
 \, will be on-site to provide information about the varieties that are best
  suited for cooking\, making apple butter\, or cider.\n\n\nEach tree costs 
 $25.00. Sale organized by the site’s non-profit organization\, the North Ca
 rolina Living Historical Farm Committee\, Inc. Money generated from the tre
 e sale helps with the upkeep of our orchard. Come out and help preserve an 
 integral part of the South’s agricultural heritage! We look forward to seei
 ng you on March 21st.\n\n\nOur trees will be sold at the Horne Creek Farm V
 isitor Center from 9 a.m. to 4 p.m. Sale starts at 9:00 am\, not before. Pa
 yment can be made by credit card\, debit card\, check\, or cash. Limit of 1
 0 trees per family. Cost per tree: $25.00. Please note: Trees are being sol
 d for home/farm use only\, not commercial endeavors.\n\n\nFor more informat
 ion about the Spring Apple Tree Sale\, please call 336-325-2298.\n\n\nHorne
  Creek Farm State Historic Site\n308 Horne Creek Farm Road\nPinnacle\, NC 2
 7043
DTEND:20260321T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030917Z
DTSTART:20260321T130000Z
GEO:36.268201;-80.484677
LOCATION:Horne Creek Living Historical Farm
