BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Guided Tours
DESCRIPTION:This outdoor guided tour offers an in-depth exploration of the 
 remarkable women honored in North Carolina Freedom Park and the powerful co
 nnections among their stories. Through compelling interpretation and histor
 ical context\, participants will discover how these leaders\, educators\, o
 rganizers\, and advocates advanced the cause of freedom in North Carolina t
 hrough courage\, intellect\, and unwavering commitment to justice.\n\nAs we
  move through the park\, we will examine how their individual journeys inte
 rsect across generations\, illuminating a broader narrative of progress roo
 ted in education\, civic engagement\, and community activism. From classroo
 ms to courtrooms\, from grassroots organizing to public leadership\, these 
 women challenged barriers and expanded opportunities not only for themselve
 s\, but for countless others.\n\nParticipants will gain a deeper understand
 ing of how these interconnected stories continue to inspire and shape our u
 nderstanding of freedom today.
DTEND:20260321T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030918Z
DTSTART:20260321T170000Z
GEO:35.78343;-78.637544
LOCATION:NC Freedom Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Through Her Voice: Women's History Tour of NC Freedom Park
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52205539852368
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/through-her-voice-womens-history-tour-
 of-nc-freedom-park
END:VEVENT
