BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:History Comes Alive with Dr. Chris Fonvielle - Stand Firm and O
 ppose the Tyranny\nSunday\, March 22\, 2026 at 10:00 AM – 11:45 AM\n\nIn co
 mmemoration of the United States’ 250th anniversary\, join Dr. Chris E. Fon
 vielle Jr.\, Professor Emeritus in the Dept. of History at UNCW\, for the f
 irst in a series of three Wilmington Water Tours’ tours that will focus on 
 the decline of the great British Empire after the French and Indian War in 
 1763\, and the rise of a great nation by 1776. We will look at the deterior
 ating relationship between the British colonies and the mother country and 
 the coming of the American Revolutionary War in the Lower Cape Fear that re
 ceived “no never mind” in Ken Burns’ 2026 “The American Revolution” documen
 tary. Did you know that the largest massed armed protest against Great Brit
 ain’s controversial Stamp Act of 1765 occurred in the Lower Cape Fear? What
  role did the 12\,000-15\,000 Scottish immigrants to southeastern North Car
 olina play in the Empire’s dissolution? Did you know that one of the Empire
 ’s most famous celebrities\, Flora MacDonald\, moved to “Scotch Country” in
  the Upper Cape Fear River Valley just prior to the Revolution?\n\nOur boat
 \, The Wilmington\, has comfortable seating for up to 49 passengers\, refre
 shments for all ages at the bar and a restroom on board. This is a 90 minut
 e cruise $45 adults\, $25 children. Boarding is 15 minutes prior.
DTEND:20260322T154500Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030918Z
DTSTART:20260322T140000Z
GEO:41.816464;-71.400624
LOCATION:Wilmington Water Tours LLC\, On the Riverwalk
SEQUENCE:0
