DESCRIPTION:Join a Ranger at the Horse Trail Parking Lot for a guided explo
 ration of some of Stone Mountain State Park's vernal pools. Vernal pools ar
 e seasonal fresh-water wetland areas that are crucial for many amphibians l
 ike wood frogs\, red-spotted newts\, and yellow-spotted salamanders to lay 
 their eggs. These pools dry up in late spring and summer and are a hotspot 
 for ecologocial activity in early spring! Please wear close-toed shoes that
  are able to get wet\, as well as appropriate clothing to wear off-trail th
 rough potentially thick vegetation. Additional materials will be provided.
DTEND:20260322T200000Z
