X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:The Limits of Freedom is a part of the America 250NC Commemorat
 ive project. America 250 is celebrating the 250th anniversary of American I
 ndependence. Limits of Freedom aims to highlight the role that enslaved ind
 ividuals had in making the nation despite being barred from the freedom the
  country proclaims.
DTEND:20260323T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030918Z
DTSTART:20260323T120000Z
GEO:36.387825;-79.756997
LOCATION:Rockingham Community College Gerald B. James Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Limits of Freedom Exhibition: Rockingham Community College
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52321912298458
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/limits-of-freedom-exhibition-rockingha
 m-community-college
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Iredell County Public Library Commemorates 250 Years of Freedom
  with Year-Long Exhibit Series\n\nThe Iredell County Public Library will ho
 st a series of four local history exhibits throughout 2026 as part of Ameri
 ca 250\, the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Indepen
 dence. The inaugural exhibit\, Visions of Freedom\, will open to the public
  on January 12 on the Main floor of the Statesville branch library.\n\nVisi
 ons of Freedom will focus on highlighting local landmarks\, Revolutionary e
 ra residents\, and important social movements that not only shaped the nati
 on\, but the Iredell County community. This free exhibit will offer a blend
  of information\, images\, and engaging interactive activities designed to 
 appeal to visitors of all ages.\n\nFor more details about the exhibit serie
 s and upcoming local history events\, please visit our website at https://i
 redell.lib.nc.us or contact Shellie Taylor at michelle.taylor@iredellcounty
 nc.gov\n\nStatesville Library Hours: M-Th 8am-8pm\, F & Sat 9am-6pm
DTEND:20260324T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030918Z
DTSTART:20260323T120000Z
GEO:35.787463;-80.88791
LOCATION:Iredell County Public Library\, Main level
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Visions of Freedom\, Exhibit #1 (Iredell County Public Library: Mai
 n Branch-Statesville)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764560103439
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/visions-of-freedom-exhibit-1-iredell-c
 ounty-public-library-main-branch-statesville
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions,Education Programs,Youth & Family A
 ctivities
DESCRIPTION:The Village of Pinehurst will be displaying two of the NC Depar
 tment of Natural & Cultural Resources exhibits throughout 2026.\n\n"Forging
  a Nation" will be on display at the Cannon Park Community Center\, 210 Rat
 tlesnake Trail\, Pinehurst\, NC 28374.\n\n"People of Colonial North Carolin
 a" will be on display at Assembly Hall\, 395 Magnolia Rd.\, Pinehurst\, NC 
 28374.\n\nThe Given Memorial Library & Tufts Archives (150 Cherokee Road\, 
 Pinehurst\, NC 28374) will also have smaller versions of the exhibits on di
 splay throughout the year and will rotate between the different exhibit sub
 jects periodically.
DTEND:20260323T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030918Z
DTSTART:20260323T123000Z
GEO:35.203585;-79.459138
LOCATION:Village of Pinehurst
SEQUENCE:0
