BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Illuminating AI series transforms cutting-edge research int
 o accessible public conversations\, showcasing the work of scientists at th
 e Renaissance Computing Institute (RENCI)\, UNC-Chapel Hill\, NC State Univ
 ersity\, the North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences (NCMNS) and Google A
 I for Nature.\n\nThis initiative examines the science underlying today’s AI
  headlines\, guiding audiences through the technology that drives artificia
 l intelligence while investigating its effects on the natural environment.\
 n\nDuring Spring 2026\, RENCI and NCMNS will co-produce three lunchtime lea
 rning sessions culminating in the April 16 Science Café: Illuminating AI Ni
 ght. Sessions are all free and open to the public.
DTEND:20260324T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030919Z
DTSTART:20260324T160000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences\, SECU Daily Planet Thea
 ter
