X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Nature & Wildlife Programs
DESCRIPTION:[Canceled Due to lack-of signups]\n \n\nCome along for a Ranger
 -led morning birding walk at Mayo River State Park. Fresh into the spring s
 eason\, enjoy the tranquil morning songs of our feathered friends while wal
 king along the unmarked Mayo Meadows trail. This trail is an easy hike thro
 ugh old tobacco fields and is about one mile out-and-back length. \n\nMeeti
 ng location is at the Mayo River Bridge Kayak Launch (3100-3110 US-220 BUS\
 , Stoneville\, NC 27048) parking lot. Please bring outdoor shoes\, binocula
 rs\, camera\, and a flash light. \n\nIf you have further questions\, please
  call the park office at (336) 916-6080. \n\nPlease note: This event is sub
 ject to cancellation due to weather.
DTEND:20260326T110000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260326T100000Z
GEO:36.438831;-79.937785
LOCATION:Mayo River Bridge Kayak Launch
