URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/limits-of-freedom-exhibition-rockingha
 m-community-college
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Iredell County Public Library Commemorates 250 Years of Freedom
  with Year-Long Exhibit Series\n\nThe Iredell County Public Library will ho
 st a series of four local history exhibits throughout 2026 as part of Ameri
 ca 250\, the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Indepen
 dence. The inaugural exhibit\, Visions of Freedom\, will open to the public
  on January 12 on the Main floor of the Statesville branch library.\n\nVisi
 ons of Freedom will focus on highlighting local landmarks\, Revolutionary e
 ra residents\, and important social movements that not only shaped the nati
 on\, but the Iredell County community. This free exhibit will offer a blend
  of information\, images\, and engaging interactive activities designed to 
 appeal to visitors of all ages.\n\nFor more details about the exhibit serie
 s and upcoming local history events\, please visit our website at https://i
 redell.lib.nc.us or contact Shellie Taylor at michelle.taylor@iredellcounty
 nc.gov\n\nStatesville Library Hours: M-Th 8am-8pm\, F & Sat 9am-6pm
DTEND:20260327T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260326T120000Z
GEO:35.787463;-80.88791
LOCATION:Iredell County Public Library\, Main level
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Visions of Freedom\, Exhibit #1 (Iredell County Public Library: Mai
 n Branch-Statesville)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764560109586
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/visions-of-freedom-exhibit-1-iredell-c
 ounty-public-library-main-branch-statesville
END:VEVENT
