BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:On March 26th at 12pm\, the New Bern Chapter of the Sons of the
  American Revolution (SAR)\, along with the Richard Dobbs Spaight Chapter o
 f the Daughters of the American Revolution (DAR) and St. John’s No. 3\, Mas
 onic Lodge (Chartered 1772 will be dedicating a “Liberty Tree” at 51 Shorel
 ine Dr\, in River Bend\, NC.  The Liberty Tree is part of the National Soci
 ety of the Sons of the American Revolution (NSSAR) Liberty Tree Project tha
 t aims to plant 250 Liberty Trees nationwide by July 4\, 2026\, honoring th
 e 250th anniversary of the U.S.  This initiative\, launched in 2023\, comme
 morates the original Boston tree\, a symbol of colonial resistance\, by pla
 cing trees and educational plagues in communities to honor Revolutionary Pa
 triots.  Everyone is invited and encouraged to attend this event. \n\nThe N
 ew Bern SAR Chapter Color Guard is planning to perform a "live fire" musket
  volley as part of the ceremony.
DTEND:20260326T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260326T160000Z
GEO:35.072228;-77.148096
LOCATION:City of River Bend\, NC
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Liberty Tree Dedication
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52276138992967
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/liberty-tree-dedication
