BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:The North Carolina State Capitol will host an educational progr
 am titled “Built To Last: The N.C. State Capitol\,” an interactive learning
  experience exploring the 19th-century trades and skilled labor that constr
 ucted the historic building between 1833 and 1840 March 27th 10 AM - 3 PM a
 ll taking place on the West grounds of the N.C. State Capitol. Event will o
 ccur rain or shine. The N.C. State Capitol is a part of the North Carolina 
 Department of Natural and Cultural Resources (DNCR). Event is free and open
  to the public. No registration required.\n\nThrough a series of interpreti
 ve stations\, visitors will learn about the craftspeople and laborers whose
  work shaped the Capitol\, including stone masons\, brickmakers\, carpenter
 s\, blacksmiths\, and coppersmiths. The program highlights how locally sour
 ced materials and specialized trades were used to construct one of North Ca
 rolina’s most recognizable historic structures. Participants will discover 
 how granite was quarried and shaped for the Capitol’s walls\, how bricks we
 re molded and fired for the building’s foundation\, and how blacksmiths for
 ged the tools necessary for construction. Additional stations will explore 
 carpentry and joinery techniques used in the building’s framework and the c
 raftsmanship behind the Capitol’s iconic copper dome. The program also emph
 asizes the diverse workforce that built the Capitol. More than 300 men work
 ed on the project\, including enslaved African Americans\, free Black craft
 smen\, immigrant laborers\, and local white workers.
DTEND:20260327T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260327T140000Z
GEO:35.780436;-78.639951
LOCATION:State Capitol
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Built To Last: The N.C. State Capitol
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52339007639015
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/built-to-last-the-nc-state-capitol-393
 4
END:VEVENT
