DESCRIPTION:Dedication of a bronze marker honoring the men and women of the
  American Revolution will occur 10:30am\, Friday\, March 27 at the Brunswic
 k County courthouse lawn. The marker\, designed and made available through 
 NSDAR\, honors all individuals who supported our country’s fight for indepe
 ndence between the Battle of Lexington on 19 April 1775 and the departure o
 f the British from New York on 26 November 1783. Brunswick County residents
  of the era were actively involved in the war in many capacities.\n\nThe ma
 rker will be placed on the east side of the courthouse lawn near the parkin
 g entrance\, and a garden will be planted at the base. County workers will 
 maintain the marker and garden.\n\nA color guard from American Legion Post 
 453 will open the ceremony which will be attended by state and county offic
 ials\, NSDAR and SAR officers and members\, and the public.\n\n \n\nChapter
  information is available on the Internet at  https://brunswicktown.ncdar.o
 rg/  and by emailing btdarregistrar@gmail.com. For a national overview\, vi
 sit www.dar.org
DTEND:20260327T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260327T143000Z
GEO:34.056384;-78.163233
LOCATION:Brunswick County Courthouse 
