DESCRIPTION:Film Screening of Natchez on Friday\, March 27th\, 2026 from 7-
 9:00pm at Orange County Public Library's Main Library located at 137 West M
 argaret Lane\, Hillsborough\, North Carolina 27278. \n\nJoin us for a speci
 al\, after hours screening of Suzannah Herbert’s 2025 documentary film\, Na
 tchez\, exploring the past and future of historic Natchez\, Mississippi whi
 ch relies on antebellum tourism to survive. A short discussion will follow 
 the film. Registration is preferred for this event. Note: The library will 
 close as normal at 6pm on this Friday. Doors will open for the event at 6:3
 0pm. Run time for this film is 1 hour and 26 minutes. Learn more about Natc
 hez and view the trailer at natchezfilm.com\n\nThis is one of Orange County
  Public Library's programs taking place throughout 2026 that commemorate Am
 erica 250\, the 250th anniversary of the nation's founding. Click here to s
 ee more A250 events at Orange County Public library.
DTEND:20260328T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260327T230000Z
