BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Outdoor & Recreation,Nature & Wildlife Progra
 ms
DESCRIPTION:What tells you it is spring? How do other kinds of organisms kn
 ow it is spring\, and what does that mean for them? Join us in looking for 
 signs of spring around Prairie Ridge for this program for adults and learn 
 how you can contribute your own observations to phenology monitoring effort
 s. Following our walk we will return to the classroom for a zine-making wor
 kshop on time\, memory\, seasons\, and the profound changes that take place
  around us each year and connect us to the more-than-human world.\nCome dre
 ssed for the weather wearing closed toed shoes and ready for a walk of abou
 t a half mile over uneven ground\, and bring a notebook and water. Zine-mak
 ing materials will be provided.
DTEND:20260328T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260328T170000Z
GEO:35.812197;-78.714552
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge Ecostation
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Signs of Spring: Memory Zines and Phenology
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52154770059259
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/signs-of-spring-memory-zines-and-pheno
 logy
END:VEVENT
