BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Theater & Musicals
DESCRIPTION:It’s the summer of 1776\, and the nation is ready to declare in
 dependence… if only our founding fathers can agree to do it! 1776 follows J
 ohn Adams of Massachusetts\, Benjamin Franklin of Pennsylvania and Thomas J
 efferson of Virginia as they attempt to convince the members of the Second 
 Continental Congress to vote for independence from the shackles of the Brit
 ish monarchy by signing the Declaration of Independence.\n\nThe seminal eve
 nt in American history blazes to vivid life in this most unconventional of 
 Broadway hits. Celebrate the semiquincentennial of the United States at 177
 6!\n\nMusic and Lyrics by Sherman Edwards\nBook by Peter Stone\nBased on a 
 concept by Sherman Edwards\nOriginal Production Directed by Peter Hunt\nOri
 ginally Produced on the Broadway Stage by Stuart Ostrow\n\nDirected by Patr
 ick Torres\n\n1776 is presented through special arrangement with Music Thea
 tre International (MTI). All authorized performance materials are also supp
 lied by MTI. www.mtishows.com\n\nPost-Show Discussion | Sunday\, April 12 @
  6pm\n\nJoin us following the Sunday\, April 12\, matinee performance for a
  post-show discussion. Details coming soon!\n\n \n\nTicket Information\n\nT
 ickets on sale now!\n\nRuntime is approximately 2 hours 45 minutes\, includ
 ing one 15-minute intermission.\n\nShow Times:\n\nFridays and Saturdays (pl
 us Thursday\, April 2) at 8:00pmSundays at 3:00pmSingle ticket prices\, exc
 luding tax and fees:\n\nAdult: $33Senior/Student/Military: $30Seniors are a
 ge 62 and up. Students are through college.
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260329
GEO:35.791719;-78.66886
LOCATION:Raleigh Little Theatre \, Cantey V. Sutton Theatre
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:1776 Musical - Sherman Edwards and Peter Stone
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52435380174104
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/1776-music-sherman-edwards-and-peter-s
 tone
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Homeschool & Education Days,Exhibits & Tours,
 Special Site Programs,Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddl
 e, hikes),Nature & Wildlife Programs,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Join the Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt at Elk Knob Sta
 te Park. Journey through northern hardwood forest\, follow winding mountain
  trails\, and explore the unique ecosystems of this high-elevation park. Ke
 ep your eyes open—what signs of wildlife or weather-shaped landscapes will 
 you uncover? Look for unique rocks that make Elk Knob a very special clue i
 n North Carolina’s geologic history. Start at the Visitor Center and scan t
 he QR code in your Actionbound app. Flyers with the QR code will be placed 
 in the Park Office and on all park map kiosks. \n\nThe adventures are avail
 able on the Actionbound app – a free download to your cellphone through you
 r phone’s app store. There’s no need to create a profile and no personal da
 ta is collected with Actionbound. You simply find new hunts by searching fo
 r the park name or scanning the associated QR code posted for your park’s a
 dventure.\n\nThis program is made possible through a partnership with the N
 C Science Trail (ncsciencetrail.org)! Visit their website for more Curious 
 Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunts being held in other NC State Parks and for 
 other programs being offered throughout the state. \n\nThis scavenger hunt 
 is running now through April 30\, 2026.
DTEND:20260330T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030920Z
DTSTART:20260329T110000Z
GEO:36.333462;-81.696432
LOCATION:Elk Knob State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Elk Knob State Park: Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52374989475442
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/elk-knob-state-park-curious-minds-adve
 nture-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
