BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260329T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030921Z
DTSTART:20260329T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082922175
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Throughout our four-day eggstravaganza\, event tickets give you
  access to our museum grounds and exhibit buildings and include a visit wit
 h the Easter Bunny! You’ll be able to take your own photos\, or for an addi
 tional charge\, have our professional onsite photographer take your family’
 s photos. Enjoy the springtime weather as you explore the museum exhibits f
 eaturing model train layouts\, trains\, airplanes\, automobiles\, trucks\, 
 and more.\n\n\nUpgrade your visit with a leisurely 25-minute train ride exp
 erience aboard our specially decorated Easter-themed train! While riding th
 e rails through our 60-acre museum site\, you’ll be greeted by the Easter B
 unny who will be passing out treats to the kids. Your ticket also allows yo
 u to visit the museum grounds and exhibit buildings. Before or after your r
 ide\, you’ll be able to enjoy a visit with the Easter Bunny and all the oth
 er activities!
DTEND:20260329T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030921Z
DTSTART:20260329T160000Z
GEO:35.687243;-80.433348
LOCATION:North Carolina Transportation Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Easter Bunny Express
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52198796913622
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/easter-bunny-express
END:VEVENT
