BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings
DESCRIPTION:Join other K-5 classroom and nonformal educators as we explore 
 Project Learning Tree activities focused on birds.\n\nTogether for Birds is
  PLT’s Newest Activity Collection!\n\nBirds are a wonderful introduction to
  the natural world and happen to be just outside your door! Whether in the 
 city or a forest\, a variety of birds are usually within easy eyeshot or ea
 rshot. The activities are designed for educators to use with students in gr
 ades K-2\, with variations for grades 3-5. The collection is filled with en
 hanced bird-specific content such as new enrichment experiences\, recommend
 ed reading\, forest facts\, accompanying posters\, and charts. Every partic
 ipant will leave with a guide of this collection.\n\nThis workshop counts t
 oward NC Environmental Education Certification (Criteria I) and consists of
  six contact hours that may count toward CEUs for teachers.\n\n \n\nLocatio
 n: Carolina Beach State Park \nWorkshop Cost: $25\nThe PLT activity guides 
 are provided free of charge to participants through support from the NC For
 estry.\nFor additional workshop information\, call 910-772-0546.
DTEND:20260407T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030922Z
DTSTART:20260407T130000Z
GEO:34.045859;-77.905159
LOCATION:Carolina Beach State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Project Learning Tree - Together for Birds
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51904311135329
