 ms,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Calling all young explorers\, nature lovers\, and future park p
 rotectors! Join the Lake James State Park Rangers for an exciting Junior Ra
 nger Program designed to help kids earn their official Junior Ranger Badge.
 \n\nKick things off by meeting our friendly Park Rangers\, who will guide y
 ou through the Junior Ranger journey and share what it’s really like to wor
 k as a ranger- protecting wildlife\, education\, firefighting\, keeping peo
 ple safe\, and helping visitors enjoy the park. Then the adventure is yours
 ! Set out to explore Lake James State Park at your own pace while completin
 g activities in the Junior Ranger Booklet along the way.\n\nOnce you’ve ear
 ned enough acorns (points)\, head back to the Visitor Center to take the Ju
 nior Ranger Oath and be officially sworn in as Lake James State Park’s newe
 st Junior Ranger—badge included!\n\nThis program is fun\, educational\, and
  perfect for curious minds of all ages. Come learn\, explore\, and discover
  why Lake James State Park is such a special place!
DTEND:20260407T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030922Z
DTSTART:20260407T200000Z
GEO:35.760718;-81.882276
LOCATION:Lake James State Park- Paddy's Creek Visitor Center
