BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Cape Fear Community College is planning a special panel discuss
 ion series as part of the nationwide celebration of America’s 250th birthda
 y\; it is looking for local veterans and military family members willing to
  share their stories.\n\nCFCC is seeking participants who served \, or the 
 family members of those who served\, during the following eras:\n\nWorld Wa
 r II\n\nKorean War\n\nVietnam War\n\nModern conflicts\, including Iraq and 
 Afghanistan\n\nThe WWII panel discussion will take place April 6\, followed
  by the Korean and Vietnam wars on April 7 and modern conflicts on April 8.
  These panels will highlight personal experiences\, service\, and reflectio
 ns across generations\, helping preserve local military history while honor
 ing those who have served.\n\nInterested participants can contact Director 
 of Veteran Services Jason Bocchino at jbocchino@cfcc.edu or 910-362-7106.
DTSTAMP:20260410T030922Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260408
GEO:34.243326;-77.948879
LOCATION:Cape Fear Community College 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:America 250 Veterans Forum
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52391639924698
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/america-250-veterans-forum
END:VEVENT
