BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:The oceans truly connect us all\, from pole to pole and around 
 the equator. The legend of the mermaid is a great representation of that co
 nnection\, one that binds seafarers the world over. The half-human\, half-f
 ish creature has appeared in many cultures throughout time and geography. A
 ssociate Education Curator Christine Brin will share some of the iconic tal
 es of mermaids\, how they have appeared in other regions of our watery plan
 et\, and the evolution the mysterious creature has undergone through the ye
 ars.\n\nThis program is part of the museum’s Maritime Heritage Lecture Seri
 es\, informal lectures focused on North Carolina’s rich maritime history\, 
 coastal environment\, and culture.  Programs are offered select Thursdays a
 t noon. The lectures are held in the museum auditorium and streamed via Zoo
 m. Admission is free\, and registration is not required for the in-person p
 rogram. Visit ncmaritimemuseumbeaufort.com/virtual to sign up to receive th
 e Zoom links. Programs are also posted to the museum’s YouTube channel.
DTEND:20260409T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030922Z
DTSTART:20260409T160000Z
GEO:34.717841;-76.666223
LOCATION:North Carolina Maritime Museum in Beaufort
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:A General History of Mermaids
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52375160941733
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/a-general-history-of-mermaids
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join this month’s Sandbar Lecture Series speaker Ann Bokelman a
 s she presents George Washington during the Revolutionary. This lecture is 
 part of a series of events to celebrate the 250th Anniversary of the signin
 g of the Declaration of Independence.\n\n\n\nGeorge Washington was an honor
 able\, brave\, and inspiring leader. Eight years of war tested him in many 
 ways. The stories behind the betrayal by Benedict Arnold and the Battle for
  Yorktown are two examples Ann presented to show us what an amazing man he 
 was.\n\nBokelman\, a Sunset Beach resident since 2007\, graduated from Ohio
  State University with both B.S.N. and M.S.N. degrees\, earned her Ph.D. in
  Adult Education from Virginia Commonwealth University\, and has retired fr
 om a career in healthcare and nursing education.
DTEND:20260409T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030922Z
DTSTART:20260409T160000Z
LOCATION:Museum of Coastal Carolina\, Lecture Hall
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Sandbar Lecture Series: George Washington during the American Revol
 ution
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52462504906843
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/sandbar-lecture-series-george-washingt
 on-during-the-american-revolution
END:VEVENT
