BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Market hunter\, wilderness scout\, frontier guide\, elected lea
 der and neighbor to the Moravians—Daniel Boone’s life reads like an adventu
 re novel. Author Randell Jones brings Boone’s extraordinary story to life\,
  examining his impact as one of America’s most legendary pioneers during th
 e American Revolution. Followed by a Q&A and book signing with the author. 
 \n\nJoin us on Saturday April 11\, 2026 at 2pm in the Gray Auditorium at th
 e Visitor Center for a riveting presentation on the life and times of Danie
 l Boone followed by a Q&A with author Randell Jones. Mr. Jones will have co
 pies of his book available for purchase following the talk. So join us to c
 elebrate the 250 years work of American stories that shape who we are today
  and learn more about your local history. Celebrate America 250 all year lo
 ng here at Old Salem Museums & Gardens!\n\nRandell Jones is an award-winnin
 g writer of several books about the pioneer and Revolutionary War eras in t
 he South\, and of North Carolina history especially. For a dozen years he s
 erved as an invited member of the Road Scholars Speakers Bureau of the NC H
 umanities Council\, speaking to audiences around the state from the coast t
 o the mountains. He has received two awards from the Kentucky Historical So
 ciety\, and from the National Society\, Daughters of the American Revolutio
 n in 2013\, he received its national History Award Medal for his body of wo
 rk. During the last 20 years\, his books\, videos\, and audio presentations
  on history have received numerous recognitions from the NC Society of Hist
 orians. For commemorating America 250 in North Carolina\, he is reprising R
 oy Thompson’s yearlong weekly series Before Liberty about North Carolina as
  a podcast on Substack. Since 2019\, Randell has written numerous articles\
 , videos\, and audios for his companion BecomingAmerica250.com website\, in
 cluding The New Kings Mountain Story Video Trilogy. Randell lives in Winsto
 n-Salem\, North Carolina.
DTEND:20260411T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260411T180000Z
GEO:36.083505;-80.24289
LOCATION:Old Salem Museums & Gardens\, Gray Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Daniel Boone Lecture 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52134087478576
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/daniel-boone-lecture
END:VEVENT
