DESCRIPTION:The history of our region traditionally centers European settle
 ments and the late 18th century battle to establish independence from Brita
 in. Less visible are the movements of peoples and the pursuit of livelihood
 s and community that existed prior to commemorated\nmilitary events and con
 tinues through present day. Explore the shifting populations and maps of th
 e region through the lens of indigenous scholarship to illuminate beyond 25
 0.
DTEND:20260411T203000Z
