BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Concerts (Music)
DESCRIPTION:For 250 years\, America has expressed its ideals of peace and f
 reedom through music—and now\, those songs are coming together in one power
 ful night. Celebrating America’s Playlist is a live concert that marks the 
 nation’s Semiquincentennial with a soundtrack that spans from 1776 to today
 .\n\nSet at the Fletcher Opera Theater in Raleigh\, this event brings local
  choirs\, soloists\, and small groups to the stage—backed by a stellar live
  band and led by a visionary music director. Each performance is paired wit
 h short narration that connects the music to defining moments in U.S. histo
 ry and to the enduring spirit of liberty that has shaped—and been shaped by
 —each generation.\n\nPresented by Crabtree Rotary and your local Rotary clu
 bs\, this is more than a concert—it’s a celebration that lets the story of 
 our nation sing through the voices of our community.
DTEND:20260412T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260411T230000Z
GEO:35.77126;-78.639608
LOCATION: A.J. Fletcher Opera Theater
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Celebrating America's Playlist: The 250-Year Soundtrack of Freedom 
 and Peace
