BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings
DESCRIPTION:The introductory wooden boatbuilding class provides hands-on ex
 perience with fundamental boatbuilding concepts. The course teaches student
 s to select wood\, design a boat\, and use various techniques like steam be
 nding\, planking (carvel or lapstrake)\, and fastening to construct a small
  boat. The curriculum covers basic design\, essential tools\, safe workshop
  practices\, and the properties of wood\, culminating in a small project th
 at builds confidence for independent boatbuilding.\n\nClass runs from 9 a.m
 . to 5 p.m. each day. Class fee is $200 ($180 for Friends of the Museum). M
 inimum age is 16. Course size is limited\, and advance registration is requ
 ired. Register online or by calling 252-504-7758.
DTEND:20260412T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260412T130000Z
GEO:34.717841;-76.666223
LOCATION:North Carolina Maritime Museum in Beaufort
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Introduction to Wooden Boatbuilding
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52375233659893
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/introduction-to-wooden-boatbuilding
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Special Site Programs
DESCRIPTION:Prior to opening to the general public\, the museum will be ope
 n for a Sensory-Friendly event. Sensory Friendly Day begins at 9 a.m. You a
 re welcome to stay as long as you wish\, however the museum will open to th
 e public at noon on Sensory Friendly Day.\n\nTrained museum educators and v
 olunteers will be stationed around the museum with specially designed inter
 active activities to create a meaningful experience at each exhibit. Sensor
 y-friendly activities are available until 1pm.\n\nSocial Narratives and map
 s are available for download on our website prior to your visit. Visual sup
 ports\, such as schedules and sensory-friendly maps will be available to he
 lp guide individuals through their preferred routes. Quiet/Calm down spaces
  will be available throughout the museum and highlighted on the provided ve
 nue map. Several sensory-friendly items will be available for sale in the G
 ift Station.\n\nWe hope to provide a fun and engaging experience for indivi
 duals of all ages\, filled with opportunities to learn\, interact\, and enj
 oy the many exhibits that we have to offer.
DTEND:20260412T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260412T130000Z
GEO:35.687243;-80.433348
LOCATION:North Carolina Transportation Museum
