BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Join the Library of North Carolina's Government and Heritage Li
 brary for a virtual webinar with the NC State University Libraries Special 
 Collections Research Center.\n\nIn this webinar\, Special Collections staff
  will be presenting on the history and legacy of North Carolina Cooperative
  Extension. NC Cooperative Extension is a state-based educational system th
 at was established in the early 20th century to bring practical knowledge f
 rom land-grant universities to local communities.\n\nThis webinar presentat
 ion will highlight a current LSTA-funded digitization project that is makin
 g NC Cooperative Extension records more accessible to the public. Spanning 
 most of the twentieth century\, these records document agricultural innovat
 ion\, educational outreach\, and community development across North Carolin
 a. Laura Lethers\, Digital Project Librarian\, will guide attendees through
  the digitized collections\, share tips for using Extension records in hist
 orical research\, and demonstrate how these materials can help researchers 
 interested in North Carolina communities and history.
DTEND:20260414T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260414T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Expanding Access to NC Cooperative Extension Records
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52567363354122
