DESCRIPTION:Full body workout mimicking animal movements. The first 5-10 mi
 nutes will focus on stretching and warming up our muscle groups. This will 
 be followed by 10 minutes of body movement practice leading into a 20-minut
 e circuit of those learned movements\, known as an AMRAP (as many rounds/re
 ps as possible). We’ll end with a 10-minute cool down. This will be physica
 lly challenging\, but movements can be modified. Meet in the open lawn near
  the Visitor’s Center. Program is weather dependent.
