BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings
DESCRIPTION:The Library of North Carolina's Government and Heritage Library
  invites you to join us for an in-person Documentary Poetry Workshop with N
 orth Carolina Poet Laureate Jaki Shelton Green. In this workshop\, Jaki She
 lton Green will facilitate a creativity salon focused on What We Keep Keeps
  Us: Exploring Our Human Museums. As we think of ourselves as our own curat
 ors or personal anthropologists\, we will explore what's in our human museu
 ms and how these primary sources shape our lives\, our values\, and our cre
 ativity.\n\nWorkshop participants are invited to bring artifacts\, photos\,
  objects\, heirlooms\, or stories that hold special meaning for them. This 
 session will include a writing exercise and discussion that examines the ma
 ny narratives\, memoirs\, short stories\, poems\, novels\, and legacies tha
 t are hidden in full sight... just waiting to be written.\n\nRegistration i
 s required and limited to 100 registrants. This event is free and open to t
 he public.\n\n\nDetails:\nDate/Time: Wednesday\, April 15\, 2026\, 6:00 PM 
 - 8:00 PM ET\nLocation: The Department of Natural and Cultural Resources (D
 NCR) Auditorium | 109 E Jones Street\, Raleigh\, NC 27601\nRegistration is 
 required and limited to 100 registrants. This event is free and open to the
  public.
DTEND:20260416T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260415T220000Z
GEO:35.78292;-78.637155
LOCATION:Department of Natural & Cultural Resources Building\, 109 E Jones 
 St. Raleigh\, NC
SEQUENCE:0
