UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52339296845435
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/first-flight-societys-celebration-of-w
 ilbur-wrights-birthday
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:During the American Revolution\, supplying the Continental Army
  was one of its greatest challenges\, and moving provisions from place to p
 lace was a constant struggle. The critical role of rough roads\, winding ri
 vers\, and thousands of draft animals is often overlooked in the story of t
 he Revolution. Discover how hundreds of North Carolinians were called into 
 service to transport essential goods across the state and beyond.\n\nJoin N
 athan Schultz for a fascinating presentation on this lesser-known side of t
 he Revolution\, including his own experiences portraying an ox driver along
  part of Henry Knox’s historic route through hands-on interpretation of tea
 mster work. If you need assistance or have any questions before registering
 \, contact Matthew McCarthy at matthew.mccarthy@dncr.nc.gov or 704-605-6282
 .\n\nThis presentation will be held in the museum’s Roundhouse Orientation 
 Room.
DTEND:20260417T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260416T230000Z
GEO:35.687243;-80.433348
LOCATION:N.C. Transportation Museum\, Roundhouse Orientation Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:"Logistics of Liberty" A250 Presentation
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52390711526239
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/logistics-of-liberty-a250-presentation
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Curious about what data science and AI bring to your life every
 day? Join us for an evening discussing exciting local research from scienti
 sts at the NC Museum of Natural Sciences\, UNC-Chapel Hill\, UNC’s Renaissa
 nce Computing Institute (RENCI)\, NC State University\, and beyond! You’ll 
 learn about exciting research using artificial intelligence and data scienc
 e methods to spark charismatic animal research\, health-related research\, 
 participatory science opportunities in your backyard and across the globe i
 n Galapagos\, Puerto Rico\, and beyond. The highlight of the evening will b
 e the Science Cafe talk and its relevance to your daily life. You’ll leave 
 the evening knowing how artificial intelligence benefits Museum research\, 
 art\, and the world around us.
DTEND:20260417T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260416T230000Z
