BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Outdoor & Recreation
DESCRIPTION:Step into the world of coastal shorebirds on this shorebird-foc
 used bird hike! Join an Aquarium naturalist for a guided walk on the beach 
 as you search for sandpipers\, plovers\, willets\, and other shoreline spec
 ialists. Learn how to spot key field marks\, identify birds by behavior and
  habitat\, and discover how tides influence where shorebirds feed and rest.
  Along the way\, you’ll pick up expert birding tips and enjoy a special up-
 close encounter with one of our bird ambassadors. Binoculars provided\, or 
 bring your own!\n\n$15 non member / $13.50 aquarium member\n\nAges 10 and u
 p. Ages 10 - 17 must be accompanied by a participating adult
DTEND:20260417T133000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030923Z
DTSTART:20260417T120000Z
