CATEGORIES:Organizational,Volunteer Opportunities
DESCRIPTION:Sign up here: https://forms.gle/LYs7AeNWk51ZEqS87\n\n\nHelp us 
 celebrate our 6th annual Earth Day Clean Up in Johnston County\, NC! Let's 
 work together to remove litter across the county\, in parks\, open spaces\,
  on trails\, and roadsides\, on Saturday\, April 18th\, from 9:00 am to 12:
 00 pm.\n\nParticipating locations include but are not limited to:\nTown of 
 Benson \nPrinceton Community Action\nBentonville Battlefield\nTown of Arche
 r Lodge\nTown of Clayton\nTown of Selma\nKenly Parks and Recreation\n\nhttp
 s://forms.gle/LYs7AeNWk51ZEqS87Cleveland Community\nHowell Woods Environmen
 tal Learning Center\nTriangle Land Conservancy's Flower Hill Nature Preserv
 e\n\nBusinesses\, churches\, youth groups\, neighborhoods\, civic groups\, 
 families\, and individuals across the county are invited to participate. \n
 \nDetails:\n- Our goal is to work with local parks and recreation departmen
 ts and nonprofit organizations in towns across the county\, as well as NC D
 OT as part of the Litter Sweep initiative.\n- Registration is required for 
 litter cleanup in public spaces.\n- Supplies will be provided at each locat
 ion as available\, but volunteers are encouraged to bring their own if they
  have them.\n\nWe look forward to working with you!
DTEND:20260418T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T130000Z
LOCATION:Johnston County
