BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a hands-on painting and illustration workshop led b
 y Caroline Paul. We'll use repurposed cardboard to share memories and exper
 iences through imagery and text\, inspired by Paul's own work — seen around
  Winston-Salem and now officially installed through a Public Art Council gr
 ant in Miller\, Washington\, and Lockland Parks. Participants can explore e
 xpressive figures\, animals\, shapes\, and messages on cardboard\, an affor
 dable and familiar material that offers an inviting surface for experimenta
 tion and communication. This all-ages workshop encourages play\, reflection
 \, and creative confidence. No experience needed\, just curiosity and a des
 ire to make something meaningful together.
DTEND:20260418T170000Z
