DESCRIPTION:In celebration of Earth Day\, join the Tobacco Farm Life Museum
  to explore ways that you can engage with nature\, right in your own backya
 rd! Learn more about the world around you from community partners like the 
 North Carolina Bluebird Society\, the Wilson County Beekeepers\, and the Wi
 lson County Master Gardeners. Participate in games and hands-on activities\
 , create crafts\, and learn about how people in the past interacted with na
 ture in their backyards. Don't forget to check out the traveling exhibit "S
 aving Our Wildflowers\," on loan from the North Carolina Botanical Gardens 
 in the gallery!
DTEND:20260418T190000Z
