BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:Join the celebration for the oldest known living longleaf pine 
 in the world\, right here at Weymouth Woods Sandhills Nature Preserve.\n\nT
 his year the Old Tree turns 478 years young!\n\n> Play games\, see live ani
 mals\, take a guided hike out to give the Old Tree a birthday hug\, and (we
 ather permitting) witness a live demonstration prescribed burn!\n\n> Learn 
 all about the unique longleaf forest ecosystem and the role that fire plays
  in keeping it healthy as you talk with conservation experts and wildlife e
 ducators.\n\n>Find great food from a variety of trucks!\n\n> See how tar\, 
 pitch\, and turpentine were made from pine resin\, and why we're known as t
 he Tar Heel State!\n\nThis event is FREE and open to the public!\n\nEvent p
 arking will be available at Weymouth Center for the Arts\, 555 East Connect
 icut Ave\, Southern Pines\, NC 28387.\n\nSee more activities and a schedule
  of events at www.partyforthepine.org
DTEND:20260418T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T140000Z
GEO:35.170298;-79.382785
LOCATION:Weymouth Woods Boyd Tract
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Party for the Pine 2026
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52558233387782
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/party-for-the-pine-2026
