BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Organizational,Volunteer Opportunities,Outdoor & Recreation,Stat
 ewide Clean Up
DESCRIPTION:“Invasive” plants are introduced\, aggressively-growing plants 
 that negatively impact local ecosystems. Join park staff at Haw River State
  Park’s Iron Ore Belt Access to help remove these leafy invaders! \n\nTypic
 al workdays start with paperwork for new volunteers (less than five minutes
 ) followed by a short hike to the work area where volunteers will receive i
 nstruction on how to identify the target species of the day. The rest of th
 e time will be used on employing hands-on\, seasonally appropriate techniqu
 es to remove invasive plants from the landscape\, helping to restore the ar
 ea for native plants and wildlife. \n\nAdvance registration is required as 
 supplies and space are limited. This opportunity is only open to volunteers
  ages 12 and up. Any volunteers under the age of 16 must be registered with
  and accompanied by an adult. \n\nVolunteers should wear long sleeves\, lon
 g pants\, and close-toed shoes. Please bring work gloves and loppers or pru
 ning shears if you have them\, but if not they will be provided (and you do
 n't need to let us know in advance either way). Meet at the parking lot of 
 the Iron Ore Belt Access.
DTEND:20260418T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
GEO:36.250909;-79.756467
LOCATION:Haw River State Park\, Iron Ore Belt Access - 6068 North Church St
 \, Greensboro\, NC
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC the Beautiful: Invasive Plant Purge
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51896970711323
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/invasive-plant-purge
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Please join us as we raise a teacup to our founding mothers. St
 ep back in time for an enjoyable afteroon while hearing from the remarkable
  women who stood beside America's founding fathers. We will meet women of w
 it\, strength\, and influence that helped shape a nation. You will enjoy an
  elegant array of food and tea while celebrating history. While not require
 d \,please feel free to wear your best colonial or regency period clothing 
 or your favorite tea party hat. Proceeds from ticket sales will go towards 
 an America 250! Scholarship to be presented to a student of Craven County C
 ommunity College.
DTEND:20260418T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
GEO:35.110718;-77.040431
LOCATION:St Johns Masonic Lodge #3
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Treasures at Tea Time
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52438283670865
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/treasures-at-tea-time
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:How are you celebrating AMERICA250NC?\nStep into history with a
  spirited stroll through Charlotte’s past.\n \n VOICES FROM THE PAST is a u
 nique living history event that invites guests to explore Charlotte’s histo
 ric cemeteries\, Settlers'\, Elmwood\, and Pinewood. Along the way\, you’ll
  meet 25 costumed storytellers who bring history to life\, sharing the amaz
 ing stories of the men and women who helped make Charlotte into what it is 
 today.\n\n VOICES FROM THE PAST is not a guided tour. It is a living histor
 y event unlike anything you've ever been to.  The storytellers are at the g
 rave of the person they are portraying. Visitors will interact with the por
 trayers as they stroll from one to another at their own pace.\n\nAMERICA250
   NC will be spotlighted throughout the day with "milestones" of Charlotte'
 s history beginning with its Declaration of Independence on May 20\, 1775.\
 n \n\nVOICES FROM THE PAST is where Charlotte's 250-year history comes aliv
 e for the day\, one story at a time. Whether you are a Charlotte native or 
 new to the city\, you will learn enjoy hearing the stories. And\, we promis
 e that before the end of the day\, you will say\, "WOW\, I didn't know that
 "!\n\n This year\, we have the honor of her Majesty Queen Charlotte helping
  us celebrate this special anniversary. Bring your cameras for a selfie wit
 h the Queen!
DTEND:20260418T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T170000Z
GEO:35.235335;-80.847966
LOCATION:Historic Elmwood Pinewood Cemetery
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:VOICES FROM THE PAST - Celebrating AMERICA250 NC
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52448129630815
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/voices-from-the-past-celebrating-ameri
 ca250-nc
END:VEVENT
