DESCRIPTION:April is the time of year when many of the wildflowers begin to
  bloom at Elk Knob State Park! Enjoy an NCSciFest event at Elk Knob by hiki
 ng with a Park Ranger on the Summit Trail to survey wildflowers. We will be
  using a couple of identification methods such as an ID guide and an app ca
 lled iNaturalist. All observations will be photographed and uploaded to iNa
 turalist and NC State Park’s Natural Resource Inventory Database.\n\nNo sur
 vey and identification experience required to participate in this program! 
 The Summit Trail is 1.9 miles one way and is moderate to strenuous. We will
  be meeting in the Summit Trail parking lot to begin. Dress appropriately t
 o hike and bring water.\n\nPlease email marissa.mabe@ncparks.gov to registe
 r for this program.
DTEND:20260418T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260418T180000Z
