BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:The Brunswick County Master Gardeners Volunteer Association wil
 l hold an online plant sale starting on April 17\, 2026 and running until A
 pril 24\, 2026 with pick up day on May 1\, 2026. This event celebrates the 
 important colonial history of Brunswick County  through education on herbs\
 , flowers\, vines\, shrubs and small trees which thrive here. Plants featur
 ed are those which our Colonial ancestors would have encountered along our 
 coast and the Cape Fear River which are native to our region and support po
 llinators. Also featured will be plants from seeds which colonists brought 
 with them from Europe and plants which recognize the contributions and life
  celebrations of the Gullah Geechee people who were enslaved in Africa to w
 ork the rice plantations along the Cape Fear River. This online plant sale 
 celebrates the cultural traditions  found in gardening in our coastal regio
 n of the State.
DTEND:20260421T130000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260420T130000Z
GEO:34.056715;-78.165769
LOCATION:Pick up 5/1/26 at Greenhouses behind Building N
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Celebrating Our Colonial Roots - Online Plant Sale
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50921813035777
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/celebrating-our-colonial-roots-online-
 plant-sale
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:In commemoration of America's 250th\, Atkins Library at UNC Cha
 rlotte presents the exhibit "Charlotte\, A Hornet’s Nest of Rebellion: An E
 nduring Legacy from the Revolutionary War to Today." Using archives and rar
 e books\, the exhibit tells the story of how Charlotte earned this reputati
 on\, tracing the history from British General Charles Cornwallis’s 1780 ret
 reat from our region to sports mascots and modern-day social activism. Plea
 se check the Atkins Library website for open hours.
DTEND:20260420T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260420T130000Z
GEO:35.305264;-80.730475
LOCATION:J. Murrey Atkins Library\, UNC Charlotte\, Atrium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Charlotte: A Hornet's Nest of Rebellion
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52313356777803
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/charlotte-a-hornets-nest-of-rebellion
END:VEVENT
