DESCRIPTION:NC State Parks is offering a free combination canoe paddle and 
 cleanup at the Lower Haw River State Natural Area on Earth Day. Paddle the 
 Haw in a tandem canoe while cleaning up trash in the river along the way. A
 fter a short introduction\, the paddle trip will launch at Bynum Mill Acces
 s and take out about 3.4 miles downstream at the US 64 Haw River Canoe Acce
 ss\, with a shuttle ride back to Bynum Mill Access. Bring your own snacks/l
 unch and drinking water for a short lunch stop along the river. NC State Pa
 rks will provide the canoes\, life jackets\, and shuttle ride.  Estimated t
 otal time for event including introduction\, lunch stop\, paddling\, and sh
 uttle ride back is approximately 4 hours total. Guide is Sean Higgins\, Int
 erpretation & Education Manager with NC State Parks. For questions\, contac
 t Sean Higgins at sean.higgins@ncparks.gov. Space is limited to 10 people. 
 Pre-registration required.  Sign up at this link:  https://forms.gle/qJdBqh
 d4Vyqk4RVK6
DTEND:20260422T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030924Z
DTSTART:20260422T140000Z
GEO:35.771669;-79.142253
LOCATION:Lower Haw River SNA - Bynum Mill Access
SEQUENCE:0
