DESCRIPTION:Bottlenose dolphins are seen in Beaufort year-round\, but they’
 re not the same individuals. We’re learning a lot from photo-ID and strandi
 ng response. Join Museum Natural Science Curator Keith Rittmaster to learn 
 about the biology\, behavior\, and conservation issues affecting “Beaufort’
 s Dolphins.”\n\nThis program is part of the museum’s Maritime Heritage Lect
 ure Series\, informal lectures focused on North Carolina’s rich maritime hi
 story\, coastal environment\, and culture.  Programs are offered select Thu
 rsdays at noon. The lectures are held in the museum auditorium and streamed
  via Zoom. Admission is free\, and registration is not required for the in-
 person program. Visit ncmaritimemuseumbeaufort.com/virtual to sign up to re
 ceive the Zoom links. Programs are also posted to the museum’s YouTube chan
 nel.
DTEND:20260423T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260423T160000Z
