DESCRIPTION:In celebration of North Carolina Library Week\, we invite membe
 rs of the public to join us for a behind-the-scenes tour of the Government 
 & Heritage Library (GHL) at the Library of North Carolina. During the tour\
 , you’ll learn more about the library’s collections and services\, discover
  research tools and resources available at the library\, and meet our knowl
 edgeable staff.\n\nThe Government and Heritage Library is a research librar
 y that provides access to information about North Carolina’s government\, h
 istory\, culture\, and people. The library offers access to genealogical re
 sources\, state publications\, digital collections\, and research support f
 or those interested in North Carolina’s history and cultural heritage.\n\nT
 his event is free and open to the public. Registration is required and limi
 ted to 15. Reserve your spot today!
DTEND:20260423T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260423T160000Z
