URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/park-hangs-blue-cactus
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts
DESCRIPTION:It’s not every day that these stand-up comedians with questiona
 ble STEM backgrounds get to fully geek out about their favorite things. Wit
 h backgrounds ranging from archaeology to engineering these funny folks are
  finally in their element at the North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences.
 \n\nThey’re not giving a dissertation. They’re not hiding behind jargon or 
 speaking in a way only a PhD could decode. This is just straight stand-up—s
 harp\, silly\, self-aware\, and occasionally way too specific. If you’re ev
 en a casual fan of science\, we’re certain this show is for you.\n\nYou mig
 ht learn something along the way. You’ll definitely hear the word “actually
 …” used with confidence.\n\n18+ Recommended. The show will begin at 7:00pm 
 in the Daily Planet Cafe. The Museum closes at 5:00pm. The Daily Planet Caf
 é will remain open after the Museum closes with a full menu.
DTEND:20260425T001500Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260424T230000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:STEM Comedy Night
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52339589059730
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/stem-comedy-night
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join the Hammocks Beach staff as we host the NC SciFest Star Pa
 rty Event:  "Mission to the Moon".  This is an after hours event filled wit
 h a variety of hands-on space-themed activities for all ages. Families can 
 build and test their own Moon landing modules\, launch stomp rockets\, and 
 construct creative Moon bases while learning about engineering and life in 
 space. Visitors can explore the night sky through telescopes\, listen to cu
 ltural sky stories during Storytelling Under the Stars\, and try challenges
  like the Rover Maze\, Lunar Twister\, and Lunar Bean Bag Toss. Additional 
 rotating activities from NC SciFest offer quick STEM experiences throughout
  the event. Together\, these stations blend science\, imagination\, and exp
 loration to inspire curiosity about our universe.
DTEND:20260425T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260424T230000Z
GEO:34.670531;-77.143056
LOCATION:Hammocks Beach State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Statewide Star Party:  Mission to the Moon
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51391896954077
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/statewide-star-party-mission-to-the-mo
 on
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Mount Jefferson State Natural Area is hosting a Statewide Star 
 Party! Join us\, Friday\, April 24th at the Sunset overlook from 7-10 pm fo
 r astronomically fun hands-on activities\, celestial crafts\, and star gazi
 ng from the overlook! Dress as an astronaut to celebrate this year’s theme\
 , “Mission to the Moon.”\n\nThe NC Science Festival’s annual Statewide Star
  Party is made possible through the generous support of the NC Space Grant.
 \n\n \n\nPhoto of the moon. Photo by R. Riddlebarger. NC Division of Parks 
 and Recreation.
