BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings,Youth & Family Activiti
 es
DESCRIPTION:Join the Museum of the Albemarle on Saturday\, Apr. 25 from 10–
 11:30 a.m. to celebrate National Coin Week as we explore the world of coins
  and their history. The theme this year is “Striking Independence: 250 Year
 s of American Numismatics.” Learn about the change in your pocket\, discove
 r coins from around the globe\, and uncover the wonders of coin collecting 
 with this free hands-on workshop for families. The workshop includes coins 
 and collecting resources for children to take with them. This program is de
 signed for grades 1–5.\n\n \n\nRegistration is required\, as space is limit
 ed. To register\, call 252-331-4054 or email noah.janis@dncr.nc.gov.\n\n \n
 \nThe Museum of the Albemarle\, a part of the Division of State History Mus
 eums\, Office of Archives and History\, is an agency of the North Carolina 
 Department of Natural and Cultural Resources.
DTEND:20260425T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260425T140000Z
GEO:36.296532;-76.219757
LOCATION:Museum of the Albemarle\, Ferebee Classroom
SEQUENCE:0
