BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History,Exhi
 bits & Tours,Special Site Programs
DESCRIPTION:Join us to commemorate the surrender negotiations at Bennett Pl
 ace that led to the largest surrender of the American Civil War. Learn more
  about how Generals Johnston and Sherman's three meetings at the Bennetts' 
 home reflected the broader national debate over how to reunite the nation &
  remake the United States without slavery. Explore how veterans\, civilians
 \, and freed people alike experienced and thought about the end of the Amer
 ican Civil War and what would come next.\n\nThis program includes several c
 ostumed interpretation events and displays.\n\nTickets must be purchased on
  site the day of the event.\n\nSchedule of Events:\n\nTalks & Presentations
 \n\n11:00  The Road to Bennett Place - Ranger Talk\n\n1:00*  The Story from
  the Land - Environmental History Walking Tour (*time may change)\n\n2:00  
 Surrender & Freedom Stories - Presentation\n\n2:30  What Comes Next?: After
 math of the Civil War - Ranger Talk\n\nSurrender Vignettes 11:30\, 11:50\, 
 12:10\, 1:20\, and 1:40\n\nLimited spaces available inside the Bennett home
 ! Be in the room where it happened while our site historians walk through t
 he surrender negotiations. Features Sherman and Johnston reenactors. (15 mi
 nutes) Advance registration link via Eventbrite - some tickets available sa
 me-day. Advanced registration recommended.\n\nFree Flowing Stations Explore
  at your own pace from 11:00 - 3:00. Most stations include hands-on educati
 on.\n\nCivil War EngineeringSignal FlagsMorse CodeCivilians on the Homefron
 tUS & Confederate soldiers at the end of the war
DTEND:20260425T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
DTSTART:20260425T150000Z
GEO:36.029293;-78.975047
LOCATION:Bennett Place State Historic Site
SEQUENCE:0
