DESCRIPTION:The 2026 NCSciFest theme is "Science Matters" and we're excited
  to talk about eleven years of bluebird conservation lessons learned by sta
 ff & volunteers at Haw River State Park. Meet in the courtyard outside of t
 he Main Lodge (building closest to flagpole) for a talk about the history o
 f bluebird conservation followed by an easy hike around Lake Loop (0.7 mile
 s) to view several different styles of nestboxes and look for baby birds. P
 lease bring comfortable walking shoes for a natural-surface travel (packed 
 dirt or gravel) and water/snacks as needed. Don't miss out on this opportun
 ity to connect with nature and expand your knowledge of the local wildlife 
 as we celebrate science in the outdoors!
DTEND:20260425T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030925Z
