DESCRIPTION:The new Introduction to Woodworking class teaches beginners to 
 safely and efficiently use hand and power tools\, understand different wood
  types and their properties\, and apply fundamental techniques like cutting
 \, shaping\, joining\, and finishing to build a small project. The course f
 ocuses on building foundational skills\, with instructor demonstrations and
  supervised hands-on practice\, to instill confidence and a solid understan
 ding for future woodworking projects.\n\nClass runs from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. e
 ach day. Class fee is $200 ($180 for Friends of the Museum). Minimum age is
  16. Course size is limited\, and advance registration is required. Registe
 r online or by calling 252-504-7758.
DTEND:20260426T210000Z
