BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Join the Chatham Community Library for this Goldston America 25
 0 Film Series\, hosted every fourth Tuesday\, January-December 2026\, 4pm-6
 pm. America 250’s mission is to honor and commemorate the 250th anniversary
  of the signing of the Declaration of Independence\, marking America’s Semi
 quincentennial. The Goldston Library will screen the following documentarie
 s and films:\n\nTue\, Jan 27\, 4pm-6pm The Congress\, Ken Burns.\nTue\, Feb
  24\, 4pm-6pm Becoming Frederick Douglass\, Stanley Nelson and Nicole Londo
 n.\nTue\, Mar 24\, 4pm-6pm Rachel Carson: The Woman Who Launched the Modern
  Environmental Movement\, Michelle Ferrari.\nTue\, Apr 28\, 4pm-6pm Thomas 
 Jefferson: A View from the Mountain\, Martin Doblmeier.\nTue\, May 26\, 4pm
 -6pm The Address\, Ken Burns.\nTue\, Jun 23\, 4pm-6pm The Brooklyn Bridge\,
  Ken Burns.\nTue\, Jul 28\, 4pm-6pm The Statue of Liberty\, Ken Burns.\nTue
 \, Aug 25\, 4pm-6pm American Coup: Wilmington 1898\, Yoruba Richen and Brad
  Lichtenstein.\nTue\, Sep 22\, 4pm-6pm How it Feels to be Free\, Yoruba Ric
 hen.\nTue\, Oct 27\, 4pm-6pm 80 Years Later\, Celine Parreñas Shimizu.\nTue
 \, Nov 24\, 4pm-6pm Gather\, Sanjay Rawal.\nTue\, Dec 22\, 4pm-6pm Women of
  World War II: The Untold Stories\, Eli Brown.\n\nThis FREE\, family-friend
 ly event is open to the public. No registration is required. The event will
  take place indoors in the Goldston Library. The Goldston Library is ADA-co
 mpliant\, including wheelchair-accessible parking\, entrances\, seating\, c
 ommon spaces\, walkways\, and restrooms. Free parking is available outside 
 the library. Pets are not allowed - please leave your furry friends at home
 .\n\nThis event is part of our Chatham Celebrates America 250 initiative. S
 ee more America 250 events.
DTEND:20260428T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260428T200000Z
GEO:35.595028;-79.328864
LOCATION:9235 Pittsboro Goldston Rd\, Goldston\, NC 27252
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Goldston America 250 Film Series
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51774187909891
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/goldston-america-250-film-series-4427
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Pretend you’ve been recruited as a member of the Culper Spy Rin
 g\, and you need to know how to decipher a message written in invisible ink
 . Supplies include a paint brush\, water\, drying cloth\, vitriol (diluted 
 sulfuric acid)\, Thomas Jefferson cipher and “furnace box.” Read the clues 
 to find the coin with a hidden message\, reveal the message using the brush
  and vitriol\, then use the cipher to decode the message.\n\nContact: Nancy
  Locquet Absillis\, nancy.locquet@naturalsciences.org
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260429
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY: Spy Training 101: Decode a Secret Message
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52504709595798
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/spy-training-101-decode-a-secret-messa
 ge
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Homeschool & Education Days,Exhibits & Tours,
 Special Site Programs,Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddl
 e, hikes),Nature & Wildlife Programs,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Join the Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt at Elk Knob Sta
 te Park. Journey through northern hardwood forest\, follow winding mountain
  trails\, and explore the unique ecosystems of this high-elevation park. Ke
 ep your eyes open—what signs of wildlife or weather-shaped landscapes will 
 you uncover? Look for unique rocks that make Elk Knob a very special clue i
 n North Carolina’s geologic history. Start at the Visitor Center and scan t
 he QR code in your Actionbound app. Flyers with the QR code will be placed 
 in the Park Office and on all park map kiosks. \n\nThe adventures are avail
 able on the Actionbound app – a free download to your cellphone through you
 r phone’s app store. There’s no need to create a profile and no personal da
 ta is collected with Actionbound. You simply find new hunts by searching fo
 r the park name or scanning the associated QR code posted for your park’s a
 dventure.\n\nThis program is made possible through a partnership with the N
 C Science Trail (ncsciencetrail.org)! Visit their website for more Curious 
 Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunts being held in other NC State Parks and for 
 other programs being offered throughout the state. \n\nThis scavenger hunt 
 is running now through April 30\, 2026.
DTEND:20260430T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260429T110000Z
GEO:36.333462;-81.696432
LOCATION:Elk Knob State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Elk Knob State Park: Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52374989514385
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/elk-knob-state-park-curious-minds-adve
 nture-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Embark on the Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt at Lake Ja
 mes State Park! Located in Burke and McDowell counties 50 miles northeast o
 f Asheville\, Lake James State Park includes two areas to access this pictu
 resque lake that are perfect for boating\, swimming\, and fishing. Campsite
 s at both Catawba River and Paddy's Creek accesses provide an opportunity t
 o spend the night by the lake\, with some sites accessible only by paddling
 . Trails include bike trails at Paddy's Creek\, the kid-friendly Holly Disc
 overy Trail\, the historic Overmountain Victory Trail\, and the Fonta Flora
  State Trail.
DTEND:20260429T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260429T120000Z
GEO:35.760718;-81.882276
LOCATION:Lake James State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Curious Minds Adventure Scavenger Hunt! 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52461739526293
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/curious-minds-adventure-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),E
 ducation Programs,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Join us all month long for NC April Science Festival with this 
 self-guided scavenger hunt up to Flat Rock View. Park at Boone Fork Parking
  Area (milepost 299.9 on the Blue Ridge Parkway)\, find the flyer by the ma
 p at the start of the trailhead\, scan the QR code in the Actionbound app\,
  and start completing the Grandfather Mountain State Park bound! The QR cod
 e is also attached to this event if you'd like to scan earlier and see what
  adventure you'll be going on.\n\nThis scavenger hunt takes you up Daniel B
 oone Scout Trail to Flat Rock View\, which is 3.6 miles round trip. The hik
 e is moderately strenuous\, and climbs 1\,050 feet up to Flat Rock View. \n
 \nThis is a self-guided hike\, please wear appropriate hiking shoes and dre
 ss for the weather.\n\nThere are no bathrooms at Boone Fork Parking Area.
DTEND:20260429T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260429T120000Z
LOCATION:Boone Fork Parking Area\, Milepost 299.9 on the Blue Ridge Parkway
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Grandfather Mountain Scavenger Hunt
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52330552614937
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/grandfather-mountain-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:StoryWalk® is simply a book and a walking path combined.  In 20
 07\, Anne Fergusson with the Vermont Department of Health had the idea to c
 ombine literacy and exercise. Teaming up with the Kellog Hubbard Library in
  Montpelier they attached laminated pages from a children’s book onto woode
 n posts.  In the ten years since\, StoryWalks have gone up in all 50 states
  and at least 11 countries. The pages are affixed to metal sign stakes and 
 a trail instantly becomes even more fun for children and book-lovers of all
  ages. StoryWalks® will usually remain up for one-to-two weeks along easy t
 rails about one mile or less. The story featured this time is called "The H
 ike" by Alison Farrell. It will be along our Cypress Point Loop Trail.
DTEND:20260430T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260429T120000Z
GEO:35.2024;-78.976116
LOCATION:Carvers Creek State Park – Long Valley Farm Access
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:StoryWalk®  - "The hike by: Alison Farrell
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52197401035302
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/story-walk-the-hike-by-alison-farrell
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Iredell County Public Library Commemorates 250 Years of Freedom
  with Year-Long Exhibit Series\n\nThe Iredell County Public Library will ho
 st a series of four local history exhibits throughout 2026 as part of Ameri
 ca 250\, the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Indepen
 dence. The inaugural exhibit\, Visions of Freedom\, will open to the public
  on January 12 on the Main floor of the Statesville branch library.\n\nVisi
 ons of Freedom will focus on highlighting local landmarks\, Revolutionary e
 ra residents\, and important social movements that not only shaped the nati
 on\, but the Iredell County community. This free exhibit will offer a blend
  of information\, images\, and engaging interactive activities designed to 
 appeal to visitors of all ages.\n\nFor more details about the exhibit serie
 s and upcoming local history events\, please visit our website at https://i
 redell.lib.nc.us or contact Shellie Taylor at michelle.taylor@iredellcounty
 nc.gov\n\nStatesville Library Hours: M-Th 8am-8pm\, F & Sat 9am-6pm
DTEND:20260430T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260429T120000Z
GEO:35.787463;-80.88791
LOCATION:Iredell County Public Library\, Main level
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Visions of Freedom\, Exhibit #1 (Iredell County Public Library: Mai
 n Branch-Statesville)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764560172084
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/visions-of-freedom-exhibit-1-iredell-c
 ounty-public-library-main-branch-statesville
END:VEVENT
