BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:What better way to celebrate America’s 250th birthday than by v
 isiting homes that witnessed that exciting time in our history.  The New Be
 rn Historical Society’s Heritage Homes Tour invites you to tour homes from 
 two historic neighborhoods.  Those in the Downtown Historic District date b
 ack to the revolutionary period and those in Riverside are inviting homes f
 rom one of New Bern’s first suburbs.  Join the crowds May 1-2\, 2026 from 1
 0am to 4pm.  Soak up the history in 10 enchanting homes in 2 historic neigh
 borhoods.\n\nEnjoy New Bern’s delightful springtime\, tour amazing homes\, 
 immerse yourself in history\, all while entertained by talented local music
 ians.\n\nTickets are available at www.NewBernHistorical.org\, at 252-638-85
 58 or at the office at 511 Broad Street.  Outlets at Mitchell hardware and 
 both New Bern Harris Teeters will open on April 1. Tickets for members\, st
 udents and active duty military are $16\, for non-members\, $19.  For group
  rates for 13 or more\, contact the office.
DTEND:20260501T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260501T140000Z
GEO:35.108209;-77.042284
LOCATION:Historic Downtown New Bern
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:New Bern Heritage Homes Tour
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51974744841317
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/new-bern-heritage-homes-tour
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260501T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260501T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082950875
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
