DESCRIPTION:You are invited to attend the 20th annual Daniel Boone Festival
  in Mocksville\, North Carolina. Every year\, Davie County puts on this eve
 nt to recognize and honor the infamous pioneer and frontiersman\, who lived
  in Davie County from 1756 until 1764.  \n\nThe Davie County Historical and
  Genealogical Society will sponsor guided tours departing at 10:15 a.m.\, 1
 2:15 p.m.\, and 2:15 p.m.\n\nStops include the Historic Joppa Cemetery\, wh
 ere members of the Boone family are buried\, the Boone Tract at Bear Creek\
 , the Daniel Boone Marker in Farmington\, Pudding Ridge\, and other signifi
 cant Revolutionary War locations.
DTEND:20260502T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030926Z
DTSTART:20260502T140000Z
GEO:35.909176;-80.578302
LOCATION:Numerous locations throughout Mocksville\, North Carolina.
SEQUENCE:0
