BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Concerts (Music)
DESCRIPTION:Storytellers is an intimate duo performance with Doni Zasloff a
 nd Eric Lindberg—a profound night of heartfelt music and mighty Jewish spir
 it.\n\nAfter over a decade of making music together as founding members of 
 progressive bluegrass band Nefesh Mountain\, Zasloff and Lindberg have crea
 ted a new and transformative acoustic experience\, writing and gathering so
 ngs and stories that have shaped their journey. This special performance ex
 plores a vast repertoire that spans seven albums of original bluegrass\, fo
 lk\, Jewish\, country\, and Americana music.\n\nThe Storytellers experience
  also features a behind-the-scenes look at the stories and inspirations fro
 m their songs\, as Zasloff and Lindberg interweave their own muses\, tales 
 from the road\, and personal experiences into the show.
DTEND:20260503T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030927Z
DTSTART:20260503T200000Z
GEO:35.807856;-78.703922
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Art
SEQUENCE:0
