BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Panels & Book Discussions
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an evening with local author Marcia Phillips as she
  delves into the rich tapestry of North Carolina's history with her book\, 
 "The Regulators in North Carolina: Prelude to the Revolution." This program
  will explore the tumultuous events of the late 1760s and early 1770s\, she
 dding light on the courageous Regulators who stood up against colonial corr
 uption and laid the groundwork for the revolution.
DTEND:20260505T230000Z
