BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks,Exhibits & Tours,Guided Tour
 s,Special Site Programs,Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, pad
 dle, hikes),Nature & Wildlife Programs
DESCRIPTION:Friends of the Blue Ridge invites outdoor enthusiasts to a uniq
 ue hiking adventure\, “Elk Knob Trails Past and Future\,” at Elk Knob State
  Park on Wednesday\, May 7th. This guided excursion will be led by NC State
  Park Ranger Marissa Mabe. As participants trek to the summit\, Ranger Mabe
  will share the rich history of the park and the surrounding mountains. Hik
 ers will also learn to identify the flora and fauna that call the Elk Knob 
 area home\, highlighting the ecological significance of this high-elevation
  landscape. In addition to exploring existing paths\, the event will featur
 e an educational discussion regarding the future of the park’s trail system
 . Highlights include an introduction to the Northern Peaks Trail\, an ambit
 ious project that will eventually connect downtown Boone to West Jefferson 
 by crossing the Amphibolite Mountains.\n\nTo ensure an intimate and educati
 onal experience\, the group size is strictly limited to 15\nparticipants. T
 o secure a spot\, visit www.blueridgefriends.org/hcregistration\n\nAbout Fr
 iends of the Blue Ridge:\nFriends of the Blue Ridge is a non-profit organiz
 ation dedicated to preserving the cultural and\nnatural resources of the Bl
 ue Ridge region through community engagement and volunteerism.\n\nParticipa
 nts MUST register for this program.
DTEND:20260507T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030927Z
DTSTART:20260507T140000Z
GEO:36.333462;-81.696432
LOCATION:Elk Knob State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Elk Knob Trails: Past and Future
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52534492858459
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/elk-knob-trails-past-and-future
END:VEVENT
