BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:As the nation celebrates 250 years of American independence\, t
 he 2026 show will aim to honor our heritage with a powerful display of airp
 ower\, patriotic unity\, and national pride.\n\n“The MCAS Cherry Point Air 
 Show is more than an aviation event\, it’s a celebration of American excell
 ence and a tribute to the strength\, innovation\, and freedom our nation ha
 s stood for over two and a half centuries\,” said Col. Brendan “Cletus” Bur
 ks\, commanding officer of MCAS Cherry Point. “In partnership with 2nd Mari
 ne Aircraft Wing and our community\, we are proud to host a world-class eve
 nt that reflects the professionalism of our Marines and the enduring bond w
 e share with Eastern North Carolina.”\n\nHeadlining the 2026 event is the r
 eturn of the legendary U.S. Navy Blue Angels\, joined by an exciting lineup
  of military and civilian acts that continue to inspire and captivate. Fan-
 favorite performances such as the jet truck\, parachute jump team\, and aer
 obatic pilots like Randy Ball\, RJ Gritter and Tom Larkin are already slate
 d to return.\n\nAs always\, the air show will be free and open to the publi
 c\, with general admission and parking offered at no cost. Premium seating 
 options will also be available for those seeking upgraded amenities. Visito
 rs can expect an immersive experience filled with aerial demonstrations\, a
 ircraft static displays\, food vendors\, and interactive exhibits for guest
 s of all ages.
DTEND:20260510T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030927Z
DTSTART:20260510T140000Z
GEO:34.883197;-76.905866
LOCATION:Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Cherry Point Air Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51276270629866
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/cherry-point-air-show
END:VEVENT
