BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),N
 ature & Wildlife Programs
DESCRIPTION:Join us on a Wildflower Walk along Upper Boone Fork Trail at Gr
 andfather Mountain State Park where you will learn how to ID common floweri
 ng species found in the Blue Ridge Mountains. This easy-moderate 1.0 mile o
 ut and back hike requires sturdy hiking boots and water. Although we won't 
 hike great distances\, we will be out in the elements the entire time\, so 
 please dress accordingly. The Southern Appalachian Mountains provide for a 
 stunning array of native wildflowers and we look forward to sharing this na
 tural beauty with you! We will meet at Boone Fork Parking Area (mile post 2
 99.9 on the Blue Ridge Parkway\, GPS:Ê36.1200\, -81.7813). There are NO bat
 hrooms. This is a Ranger Workshop with The Town of Seven Devils.
DTEND:20260513T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030927Z
DTSTART:20260513T173000Z
GEO:36.569351;-80.907868
LOCATION:Boone Fork Parking Area
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ranger Workshop - Wildflower Walk
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51815547816091
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ranger-workshop-wildflower-walk
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:In honor of the 250th anniversary of The United States\, the En
 richment Center of Lee County\, NC will be offering a three-week video-base
 d course. Professors of history and politics will guide us on a journey to 
 the New World and discover the origins of the American spirit. This course 
 consists of six documentary episodes (2 episodes per week). Complete the ep
 isodes and the accompanying quizzes to receive the certificate of completio
 n. \n\n\nWeek 2: Wednesday\, May 13\, 2026\, 2:00 - 4:00 p.m. - Nature and 
 Liberty & Frontier Wars\n\n\nThe Enrichment Center of Lee County hosts acti
 vities and events for adults age 50+.
DTEND:20260513T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030927Z
DTSTART:20260513T180000Z
GEO:35.468327;-79.158555
LOCATION:The Enrichment Center of Lee County\, NC
SEQUENCE:0
