BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Concerts (Music)
DESCRIPTION:Come\, be a part of history!\nThe Psalm of Joy will be presente
 d at the Raleigh Moravian Church\, May 17\, 2026 at 3:00pm. The concert/ser
 vice of music and word is free. An informative talk will precede the concer
 t at 1:30pm with a band prelude at 2:30pm. Psalm of Joy is an ode (a servic
 e of word and music) created by Moravian composer Johann Friedrich Peter (1
 746–1813) and performed on July 4\, 1783\, as part of the first organized J
 uly 4th celebration in the nation. \nThis year we are celebrating the 250th
  anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Independence. After years
  of suffering and turmoil\, the end of the Revolutionary War found the Mora
 vians citizens of a brand-new nation. When the Moravians in North Carolina 
 received a letter from Governor Alexander Martin (ca. 1739–1807) proclaimin
 g July 4th a day of celebration and thanksgiving\, the Moravians turned (as
  they always do) to music. Rather than revel in victory\; however\, it was 
 the return of peace that spoke to them and inspired the music of this joyfu
 l work. Whether it is in regard to the end of armed conflicts or a respite 
 from the chaos of everyday life\, this message of gratitude\, peace\, and j
 oy endures.\nTalk: History of the Psalm of Joy\, Sunday 1:30pm\nMoravian Ba
 nd Prelude\, 2:30pm\nConcert / Service – Sunday 3:00pm (about 50 minutes)\n
 Want to learn the music and participate in the choir or the band? All are w
 elcome on Saturday\, May 16. Please find all the details and register at ht
 tps://moravianmusic.org/psalm-of-joy-raleigh/
DTEND:20260517T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
DTSTART:20260517T190000Z
GEO:35.813378;-78.68264
LOCATION:Raleigh Moravian Church\, sanctuary
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Psalm of Joy
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52560463473947
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/psalm-of-joy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Concerts (Music)
DESCRIPTION:May is nationally recognized as a time to focus on mental healt
 h and well-being. To explore the powerful connection between healing and ar
 t\, join us for an evening with seven-time Grammy-nominated performing arti
 st Nnenna Freelon.\n\nThroughout this evening author event\, Freelon guides
  the audience through an intimate blend of music\, spoken word\, and storyt
 elling that reflects on love\, loss\, and the creative process. The program
  connects to her latest book\, Beneath the Skin of Sorrow: Improvisations o
 n Loss\, which invites readers into a thoughtful conversation about how gri
 ef and creativity intersect\, drawing from the rich traditions of Black her
 itage and the expressive language of jazz.\n\nTicket purchase includes acce
 ss to the event. Refreshments will be available for purchase during the sho
 w. Attendees will also enjoy special pricing and author signing of the book
  Beneath the Skin of Sorrow: Improvisations on Loss.\n\nPlease enter throug
 h the front doors of West Building.
DTEND:20260517T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
DTSTART:20260517T213000Z
GEO:35.807856;-78.703922
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Art
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:She Sings\, She Speaks: Beneath the Skin with Nnenna Freelon
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52463262601204
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/she-sings-she-speaks-beneath-the-skin-
 with-nnenna-freelon
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Pretend you’ve been recruited as a member of the Culper Spy Rin
 g\, and you need to know how to decipher a message written in invisible ink
 . Supplies include a paint brush\, water\, drying cloth\, vitriol (diluted 
 sulfuric acid)\, Thomas Jefferson cipher and “furnace box.” Read the clues 
 to find the coin with a hidden message\, reveal the message using the brush
  and vitriol\, then use the cipher to decode the message.\n\nContact: Nancy
  Locquet Absillis\, nancy.locquet@naturalsciences.org
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260518
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY: Spy Training 101: Decode a Secret Message
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52504709621417
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/spy-training-101-decode-a-secret-messa
 ge
END:VEVENT
