BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Four Historians share stories about the role NC colony played i
 n the revolutionary war.  This is a FREE event.\n\n       WELCOME – 1:00   
    \n\nSPEAKERS – 1:05 pm\n\nMike Goodwin\n“Cowpens and Kings Mountain – Am
 erica's first Civil War" \n\nBill Barber\n"Defending the Coast: the NC Inde
 pendent Seacoast Companies"\n\n \n\nCOFFEE BREAK – 2:05 pm\n\n\nSPEAKERS – 
 2:20 pm \n\nEarl Ijames\n"Naval Stores\, Real Tar Heels\, and the History a
 nd Preservation of\nour Long Leaf Pine Forest” \n\nChris Barber\n"Forgotten
  Patriots of the Albemarle"
DTEND:20260521T071500Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
