BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special program that explores Black military hist
 ory through Black GI Joe action figures. Free with admission to the doll\, 
 toy & miniature museum! 2 timeslots.\n\nEnjoy an all-ages PowerPoint presen
 tation from presenter Les Albers\, a military veteran\, historical interpre
 ter\, and re-enactor.\n\nLes will use a display of thirteen 12-inch GI Joe 
 figures to trace the Black military experience from 1778 through 2003.\nEac
 h GI Joe figure represents a chapter in American history.\n\nYou’ll learn t
 he names and stories of real Black servicemen and servicewomen\, the milita
 ry conflicts in which they served\, and the evolution of military uniforms 
 across multiple centuries.\n\nYou’ll also learn the historical significance
  of Black GI Joe figures with a spotlight on their development between 1965
  and 1997.\n\nAppropriate for all ages. Offered in-person only (though we h
 ope to replicate as an online experience in the future!)\n\nDate & Location
 :\nSaturday\, May 30\, 2026\n2 timeslots. The same program will be presente
 d in each timeslot:\n11 am to 11:40 am\n1 pm to 1:40 pm\n\nAt the NC Museum
  of Dolls\, Toys & Miniatures at 440 South Salisbury Avenue\, Spencer\, NC 
 28159\n\nCost & Registration:\nFREE with museum admission. No registration 
 is required. Just pay admission to the museum at the door when you arrive (
 cash or card).\nAdmission ranges from $5 to $10 per person.\nAdmission to o
 ur museum is always free for museum members\, so consider becoming a museum
  member! It’s a huge source of annual support to our nonprofit!
DTEND:20260530T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
DTSTART:20260530T150000Z
GEO:35.68939;-80.43524
LOCATION:N.C. Museum of Dolls\, Toys & Miniatures
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Learning Black Military History with GI Joes
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52390738888757
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/learning-black-military-history-with-g
 i-joes
END:VEVENT
