BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Spoken Word/Readings
DESCRIPTION:Step into the beautiful tradition of Appalachian storytelling w
 ith a special evening featuring legendary storyteller Orville Hicks! Known 
 for his mesmerizing way with words and deep roots in mountain folklore\, Or
 ville will share classic Jack Tales and other local legends that have been 
 passed down for generations.\n\nBut the fun doesn’t stop there! Following O
 rville’s performance\, we’re hosting a Tall Tale Contest\, where YOU can ta
 ke the stage. Whether you’re a seasoned storyteller or just want to try you
 r hand at spinning a wild yarn\, this is your chance to showcase your creat
 ivity. The taller the tale\, the better!
DTEND:20260530T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030928Z
DTSTART:20260530T160000Z
GEO:36.208683;-81.669982
LOCATION:Hickory Ridge History Museum
SEQUENCE:0
