BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:In commemoration of America's 250th\, Atkins Library at UNC Cha
 rlotte presents the exhibit "Charlotte\, A Hornet’s Nest of Rebellion: An E
 nduring Legacy from the Revolutionary War to Today." Using archives and rar
 e books\, the exhibit tells the story of how Charlotte earned this reputati
 on\, tracing the history from British General Charles Cornwallis’s 1780 ret
 reat from our region to sports mascots and modern-day social activism. Plea
 se check the Atkins Library website for open hours.
DTEND:20260608T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260608T130000Z
GEO:35.305264;-80.730475
LOCATION:J. Murrey Atkins Library\, UNC Charlotte\, Atrium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Charlotte: A Hornet's Nest of Rebellion
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52313356834172
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/charlotte-a-hornets-nest-of-rebellion
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions,Organizational,Celebrations & Comme
 morations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries,Open Houses
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to explore the history of Davie County as the S
 emiquincentennial draws closer. There will be historical artifacts on displ
 ay representing the county's history. This includes a portrait of Continent
 al Army Colonel William R. Davie\, the county's namesake. There's also a lo
 t of information on Daniel Boone\, who lived in Davie County for seven year
 s. His parents are buried in Mocksville's Joppa Cemetery. Feel free to brow
 se around the room and examine historical records and documents\, including
  a list of those who served during the American Revolution. \n\nThese artif
 acts and documents are located inside the Martin-Wall History Room within t
 he Davie County Public Library in Mocksville. This room acts as the Davie C
 ounty history museum. Paying a visit will allow you to explore the county's
  long and proud history while gaining a better understanding of the Semiqui
 ncentennial's significance. These artifacts will be on display from Monday\
 , March 16\, until at least Sunday\, July 6.
DTEND:20260608T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260608T130000Z
GEO:35.897815;-80.5597
LOCATION:Davie County Public Library\, Martin-Wall History Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:History on Display
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52372920420213
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/history-on-display
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions,Education Programs,Celebrations & C
 ommemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:The North Carolina African American Heritage Commission is loan
 ing Lake Norman State Park their Oasis Spaces traveling exhibit.\n\nTo cont
 inue the celebrate Juneteenth all month long\, stop by our auditorium to le
 arn all about The Negro Motorist Green Book. Each display panel highlights 
 a North Carolina business owner and traveler.
DTEND:20260608T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260608T130000Z
GEO:35.67247;-80.932577
LOCATION:Lake Norman State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Oasis Spaces: Navigating Jim Crow Traveling Exhibit
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52471802150792
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/oasis-spaces-navigating-jim-crow-trave
 ling-exhibit
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Its that time of year again! Come celebrate the summer at Merch
 ants Millpond State Park with our 4th year of the Summer Junior Adventure S
 eries! In this series\, we have a different topic that we teach about every
  Monday at 10 AM throughout the summer. \n\nThis week we will look into som
 e of the skills that got humanity to where we are now\; Navigation. We will
  cover ways of using navigation tools like maps and a compass\, as well as 
 why they are important skills to have before going out to put our skills to
  the test. \n\nThis program will start promptly at 10 AM at the visitor cen
 ter. Guests are encouraged to dress for the weather as part of this program
  will be outside.
DTEND:20260608T150000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260608T140000Z
GEO:36.437278;-76.701271
LOCATION:Merchants Millpond State Park\, Visitor Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ranger Katie's Cool Compass Course
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52558290256344
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ranger-katies-cool-compass-course
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:The 250th Anniversary of our great nation is upon us\, and ther
 e are many aspects of our history that we may not know.   For example\, our
  American flag has evolved and changed many times over the years.  Have you
  ever wondered what our very first flag looked like\, and how and why it ch
 anged during the time of our American Revolution?  Members of the New Bern 
 Chapter of the Sons of the American Revolution will display and share some 
 of the exciting history behind our flag\, as well as other interesting info
 rmation\, during their presentation on June 8\, 2026\, at 4:30 pm.  For mor
 e information\, please contact us at 252-566-3772 or at lagrange@neuselibra
 ry.org.
DTEND:20260608T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260608T203000Z
GEO:35.305107;-77.787537
LOCATION:La Grange Public Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Flags of the American Revolution
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51843821773945
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/flags-of-the-american-revolution
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Pretend you’ve been recruited as a member of the Culper Spy Rin
 g\, and you need to know how to decipher a message written in invisible ink
 . Supplies include a paint brush\, water\, drying cloth\, vitriol (diluted 
 sulfuric acid)\, Thomas Jefferson cipher and “furnace box.” Read the clues 
 to find the coin with a hidden message\, reveal the message using the brush
  and vitriol\, then use the cipher to decode the message.\n\nContact: Nancy
  Locquet Absillis\, nancy.locquet@naturalsciences.org
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260609
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY: Spy Training 101: Decode a Secret Message
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52504709649087
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/spy-training-101-decode-a-secret-messa
 ge
END:VEVENT
