BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),N
 ature & Wildlife Programs
DESCRIPTION:Come learn how to ID common species of trees and shrubs found h
 ere in the Blue Ridge Mountains. Learn how to ID based on leaves\, bark\, b
 uds\, and growth! Feel free to bring a notebook and pencil to take notes an
 d leaf or bark rubbings. This hike will be at Otter Falls and will be 1.2 m
 iles long. Please wear appropriate hiking footwear and bring snacks and wat
 er. This is a Ranger Workshop hosted with The Town of Seven Devils.
