BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the spirit of a nation at Stars\, Stripes\, and Sound
 s on June 14th from 4:00 PM to 8:00 PM at Jacksonville Commons—an unforgett
 able evening of music\, patriotism\, and community in honor of America’s 25
 0th.\n\nThis prestigious concert will feature a powerful collaboration betw
 een the renowned 2nd Marine Division Band and the distinguished Band of Ame
 rica’s Few. Together\, they will deliver a stirring performance filled with
  patriotic favorites\, timeless classics\, and inspiring musical tributes t
 hat honor the legacy and future of our nation.\n\nGuests can enjoy a festiv
 e atmosphere with a variety of food trucks\, America 250th-themed vendors\,
  and a beer garden offering refreshing beverages for purchase. Whether you'
 re coming for the music\, the celebration\, or the community spirit\, there
 ’s something for everyone to enjoy.\n\nBe sure to bring a lawn chair or bla
 nket to relax and comfortably take in this special evening under the open s
 ky.\n\nJoin us as we celebrate 250 years of America with music\, pride\, an
 d unforgettable moments at Stars\, Stripes\, and Sounds.
DTEND:20260615T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260614T200000Z
LOCATION:Jacksonville Commons Festival Grounds
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Stars\, Stripes\, and Sounds: Celebrating 250 Years of America
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52559600487833
