BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:In commemoration of America's 250th\, Atkins Library at UNC Cha
 rlotte presents the exhibit "Charlotte\, A Hornet’s Nest of Rebellion: An E
 nduring Legacy from the Revolutionary War to Today." Using archives and rar
 e books\, the exhibit tells the story of how Charlotte earned this reputati
 on\, tracing the history from British General Charles Cornwallis’s 1780 ret
 reat from our region to sports mascots and modern-day social activism. Plea
 se check the Atkins Library website for open hours.
DTEND:20260615T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260615T130000Z
GEO:35.305264;-80.730475
LOCATION:J. Murrey Atkins Library\, UNC Charlotte\, Atrium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Charlotte: A Hornet's Nest of Rebellion
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52313356841347
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/charlotte-a-hornets-nest-of-rebellion
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions,Organizational,Celebrations & Comme
 morations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries,Open Houses
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to explore the history of Davie County as the S
 emiquincentennial draws closer. There will be historical artifacts on displ
 ay representing the county's history. This includes a portrait of Continent
 al Army Colonel William R. Davie\, the county's namesake. There's also a lo
 t of information on Daniel Boone\, who lived in Davie County for seven year
 s. His parents are buried in Mocksville's Joppa Cemetery. Feel free to brow
 se around the room and examine historical records and documents\, including
  a list of those who served during the American Revolution. \n\nThese artif
 acts and documents are located inside the Martin-Wall History Room within t
 he Davie County Public Library in Mocksville. This room acts as the Davie C
 ounty history museum. Paying a visit will allow you to explore the county's
  long and proud history while gaining a better understanding of the Semiqui
 ncentennial's significance. These artifacts will be on display from Monday\
 , March 16\, until at least Sunday\, July 6.
DTEND:20260615T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260615T130000Z
GEO:35.897815;-80.5597
LOCATION:Davie County Public Library\, Martin-Wall History Room
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:History on Display
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52372920425340
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/history-on-display
END:VEVENT
