 ling-exhibit
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:Its that time of year again! Come celebrate the summer at Merch
 ants Millpond State Park with our 4th year of the Summer Junior Adventure S
 eries! In this series\, we have a different topic that we teach about every
  Monday at 10 AM throughout the summer. \n\nThis week we'll talk about the 
 often overlooked macroinvertebrates we have here at the Millpond! These tin
 y critters are rarely given a second thought but they contribute to the eco
 system in a big way! Whether its forming the backbone of the food web\, or 
 being an indicator for certain things\, these creatures are worth taking a 
 look at\, so come join us as we look more at our macroinvertebrates!  \n\nT
 his program will start promptly at 10 AM at the visitor center. Guests are 
 encouraged to dress for the weather as part of this program will be outside
 . This program will involve dip netting at the boat launch and particpates 
 usually get a little wet in the process.
DTEND:20260615T150000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260615T140000Z
GEO:36.437278;-76.701271
LOCATION:Merchants Millpond State Park\, Visitor Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ranger Cody' Marvelous Macroinvertebrates
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52558355731850
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ranger-cody-marvelous-macroinvertebrat
 es
END:VEVENT
