BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Panels & Book Discussions
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the June meeting of the America 250 NC Virtu
 al Book Club! We will be discussing Tobacco Wives by Adele Myers on June 17
 th at 6p.\n\nThis historical fiction novel is set in 1940s North Carolina\,
  when a young woman discovers dangerous secrets about big tobacco...all in 
 a town that relies on a tobacco economy. \n\nPlease read the book prior to 
 the discussion. We recommend borrowing from your local library. \n\nFree an
 d open to the public. No membership required. Come to whichever book talks 
 spark your interest. \n\nMeeting Link\n\nMore Information\n\nSign up for an
  Email Reminder
DTEND:20260617T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART:20260617T220000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Virtual Book Club: Tobacco Wives by Adele Myers
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51089808191712
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/virtual-book-club-tobacco-wives-by-ade
 le-myers
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Pretend you’ve been recruited as a member of the Culper Spy Rin
 g\, and you need to know how to decipher a message written in invisible ink
 . Supplies include a paint brush\, water\, drying cloth\, vitriol (diluted 
 sulfuric acid)\, Thomas Jefferson cipher and “furnace box.” Read the clues 
 to find the coin with a hidden message\, reveal the message using the brush
  and vitriol\, then use the cipher to decode the message.\n\nContact: Nancy
  Locquet Absillis\, nancy.locquet@naturalsciences.org
DTSTAMP:20260410T030929Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260618
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
