DESCRIPTION:The Pioneer Heritage Festival will promote Haywood County's ear
 ly pioneer history.  Heritage demonstrations will be held on the grounds of
  the Shelton House Museum with artisans showcasing the skills that were nee
 ded for daily living in the early 1800s.  Exhibits depicting North Carolina
 's role in the American Revolution will be on display in the Shelton House 
 barn.  Members of SAR and DAR will be onsite to help visitors learn how to 
 identify ancestors who fought in the American Revolution.  The Festival is 
 free and includes food trucks\, live music\, activities for kids\, and Shel
 ton House Museum tours.
