BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Parades & Community Celebrations,C
 eremonies & Anniversaries,Outdoor & Recreation,Education Programs,Youth & F
 amily Activities
DESCRIPTION:The Town of Duck 4th of July parade and community celebration h
 onors the nation’s founding\, connects national history to local traditions
 \, promotes civic pride\, celebrates American culture\, and offers an engag
 ing platform for education and reflection. By bringing people together acro
 ss generations\, the event reflects the spirit of unity and shared heritage
  at the heart of the America 250 commemoration.\n\n \n\nThe annual one-mile
  parade route begins at the crest of the hill on Scarborough Lane\, travels
  east towards the ocean\, turns left onto Ocean Way\, and then continues on
 to Christopher Drive to end at Pamela Court. Please note: no part of the pa
 rade will take place on Duck Road.\n\n \n\nA Community Celebration will be 
 held immediately following the parade at the Duck Town Park. The celebratio
 n will feature live music\, cold refreshments\, including watermelon provid
 ed by Green Acres Farm Market\, and the awarding of the parade trophies.\n\
 nAwards Categories to include:– Mayor’s Award– Best Local Business Entry Aw
 ard– Best Community Entry Award– Spirit Award\n\n \n\nLearn more: 4th of Ju
 ly Celebration - Town of Duck\, North Carolina
DTEND:20260703T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030931Z
DTSTART:20260703T130000Z
GEO:36.161731;-75.74778
LOCATION:Town of Duck
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Town of Duck 4th of July Parade and Community Celebration
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52399432498836
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/town-of-duck-4th-of-july-parade-and-co
 mmunity-celebration
END:VEVENT
