 ties
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Independence Day and the nation’s Semiquincentennial 
 with Island Farm! Island Farm will host visitors to celebrate the holiday. 
 Attendees are encouraged to bring a picnic lunch to enjoy on the Farm’s gra
 ssy lawn\, and continue celebrations of the nation’s birth with musket-fire
 \, traditional games\, a reading of the Declaration of Independence\, and m
 uch more.\n\n \n\nA living history farm\, Island Farm is a tangible glimpse
  into coastal history\, and the realities of life on Roanoke Island in the 
 mid-1800’s. Admission to the site is $11\, and children 3 and under are adm
 itted for free. The site is located at 1140 N US Highway 64\, north of Mant
 eo on Roanoke Island.\n\nIsland Farm is owned and operated by Outer Banks C
 onservationists\,  non-profit organization founded in 1980 to protect impor
 tant natural\, cultural\, and historic resources along North Carolina’s Out
 er Banks through education and conservation. For more information\, visit h
 ttps:obcinc.org/visit-our-sites/island-farm/\, email info@obcinc.org or cal
 l 252-473-6500.
DTEND:20260704T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030931Z
DTSTART:20260704T130000Z
