 ions & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs,Parades & Community Celebrations,Ce
 remonies & Anniversaries,Outdoor & Recreation
DESCRIPTION:You are invited to attend the annual Fourth of July Celebration
  at Davie County Community Park in Mocksville. The gate will open at 4:30 p
 m. Admission is free\, but attendees will still need to pay for food and be
 verages from the variety of food trucks that will be present.\n\nFrom 6:30 
 pm until 9:30 pm\, there will be a live performance at the park's amphithea
 ter by Chris Taylor & The Rumor\, as well as The Resistance. \n\nImmediatel
 y afterward\, there will be a pyrotechnic fireworks performance\, the bigge
 st one the region has to offer.\n\nPlease join us as we celebrate the 250th
  birthday of our great and proud nation!\n\nOn a side note\, the park is lo
 cated on the site of the previous county high school\, which opened in 1956
  and was relocated in 2017. Feel free to walk around and look for traces of
  it still present.
DTEND:20260705T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260704T203000Z
GEO:35.872281;-80.551886
LOCATION:Davie County Community Park\, Amphitheater  
SEQUENCE:0
