BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries,Outdoor
  & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes)
DESCRIPTION:To celebrate the Fourth of July\, Kill Devil Hill's hosts a fir
 eworks show. In honor of America’s 250th\, the 2026 fireworks display will 
 be bigger than before! Fireworks are launched from the end of a popular fis
 hing pier in the center of Kill Devil Hill's.\n\n \n\nResidents and visitor
 s are invited to visit one of our many beach accesses\, where beach chairs 
 can be set up to watch the spectacular show. \n\n \n\nFireworks have long b
 een a national symbol of Independence Day\, representing both celebration a
 nd remembrance\, and it provides a shared civic experience that brings the 
 community together as we publicly commemorate the signing of the Declaratio
 n of Independence.\n\n \n\nFor more information visit: https://www.kdhnc.co
 m/1014/Special-Events
DTEND:20260705T014000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260705T011500Z
GEO:36.044242;-75.674482
LOCATION:Kill Devil Hills
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Town of Kill Devil Hills: Independence Day Fireworks Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52399630336310
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/town-of-kill-devil-hills-independence-
 day-fireworks-show
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Parades & Community Celebrations,C
 eremonies & Anniversaries,Education Programs,Outdoor & Recreation,Youth & F
 amily Activities
DESCRIPTION:Fireworks are a classic symbol of independence and celebration.
  The event visually represents the ideals of liberty and the excitement of 
 freedom\, allowing the community to reflect on America’s history and values
  in a shared\, awe-inspiring experience. The Fourth of July Fireworks bring
  the community together to commemorate the nation’s founding\, creating a s
 hared moment of celebration that honors American heritage. In the context o
 f America’s 250\, the fireworks highlight 250 years of independence and the
  enduring spirit of freedom\, patriotism\, and unity that have shaped the n
 ation.\n\n \n\nLearn more: https://nagsheadnc.gov/614/Events\n\n \n\nQuesti
 ons? Contact Katie Anzalone\, Town of Nags Head Deputy Town Clerk\, at kati
 e.anzalone@nagsheadnc.gov or (252) 449-2021.
DTEND:20260705T015000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260705T012000Z
GEO:35.973164;-75.63158
LOCATION:Nags Head
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Nags Head: Fourth of July Fireworks Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52399654045689
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/nags-head-fourth-of-july-fireworks-sho
 w
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:Pretend you’ve been recruited as a member of the Culper Spy Rin
 g\, and you need to know how to decipher a message written in invisible ink
 . Supplies include a paint brush\, water\, drying cloth\, vitriol (diluted 
 sulfuric acid)\, Thomas Jefferson cipher and “furnace box.” Read the clues 
 to find the coin with a hidden message\, reveal the message using the brush
  and vitriol\, then use the cipher to decode the message.\n\nContact: Nancy
  Locquet Absillis\, nancy.locquet@naturalsciences.org
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
