BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260709T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260709T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207083005206
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts
DESCRIPTION:Travel back to 1770s–1780s Cumberland County\, North Carolina\,
  when tensions are rising and the American colonies are on the brink of rev
 olution. In this immersive tabletop role-playing game\, you’ll step into th
 e shoes of local citizens navigating loyalty\, rebellion and survival durin
 g a pivotal moment in history.\n\nExplore real historical events\, regional
  battles and political intrigue as you make choices that shape your story. 
 Will you side with the Patriots\, remain loyal to the Crown or try to survi
 ve somewhere in between?\n\nNo prior role-playing experience is necessary—j
 ust bring your imagination and your sense of adventure.\n\nRegistration is 
 required by calling 910-483-7727\, ext. 1365\, or registering online.
DTEND:20260710T003000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260709T220000Z
GEO:35.044702;-78.937485
LOCATION:Game On! Cards and Coffee
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:TTRPG: Revolutionary Cumberland 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52267679939401
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ttrpg-revolutionary-cumberland
END:VEVENT
