BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),N
 ature & Wildlife Programs,Education Programs,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we hike down to Otter Falls (1.2 miles round trip) t
 o learn about how living and non-living things interact in mountain streams
 . What are all of those insects and other critters swimming and crawling th
 rough the creek? We will catch and identify what type of creature they are 
 and what these species could tell us about water quality. Nets will be prov
 ided. Any participants wanting to get into the stream should bring clothes 
 and shoes that can get wet and a towel to dry off. Make sure to bring water
  for the hike! No pets please. This is a Ranger Workshop with The Town of S
 even Devils.
DTEND:20260715T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260715T170000Z
GEO:36.149669;-81.808644
LOCATION:Otter Falls Trail
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ranger Workshop - Stream Ecology
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51815547918503
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ranger-workshop-stream-ecology
END:VEVENT
