CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings,Outdoor & Recreation,Ou
 tdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes)
DESCRIPTION:Registration Required at Go Outdoors website: North Carolina WR
 C License - View Event. It is recommended to attend 'Learn to Fly-Fish: Bef
 ore the Cast' prior to the this program (10am-12pm same date/location). Thi
 s workshop is open to those 16 years and older. All minors must be accompan
 ied by an adult.\n\nJoin in and learn the basic principles of fly-casting! 
 This hands-on session is perfect for beginners or those looking to refine t
 heir skills. We'll cover essential techniques such as the basic overhead ca
 st\, roll cast\, and line management\, while gaining insights into proper f
 orm and equipment use. This class provides guidance to help you build confi
 dence and enjoy the art of fly fishing. All equipment is provided\, so just
  bring your enthusiasm and get ready to cast without worry!
DTEND:20260719T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
