 s,Reenactments & Living History,Exhibits & Tours,Special Site Programs,Yout
 h & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Join us as we explore the lives of sailors\, merchants\, and po
 rt towns during the Revolutionary War. Living history\, munitions demonsttr
 ations\, music and more.
DTEND:20260725T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260725T140000Z
GEO:35.476994;-76.811651
LOCATION:Historic Bath\, Bonner Point
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:250th Patriot Maritime Defense in NC
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51515262863013
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/250th-patriot-maritime-defense-in-nc
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:How did colonists prepare their households for the seasons? Wha
 t was bathing and hygiene like? How did soldiers clean their wool uniforms?
  How were plants and herbs used to freshen things up? Join our costumed int
 erpreters as they demonstrate practices of cleanliness in the 18th and 19th
  centuries. FREE. All ages welcome. Drop-in.
DTEND:20260725T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260725T140000Z
GEO:35.979741;-79.992174
LOCATION:High Point Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Getting Colonial Clean in the Historical Park
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51825907202933
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/getting-clean-in-the-park-in-the-histo
 rical-park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:Learn about the lives of sailors who will become a part of our 
 new nation’s defense and what a local seaport was like. The formal navy of 
 the colonies was small\, by 1776 there were just 27 colonial warships\, but
  the number of support vessels operating as privateers was over 1600 and be
 came an important factor in our victory. At Bath\, you would have seen rope
 making\, shipping of vital naval stores\, boat work\, and spinning and weav
 ing of cloth for sailmaking. Townspeople with their families. Drop by the T
 avern for talk of the simmering war and outrage over British impressment of
  sailors. DNCR America 250th airstream staff. Munitions demonstrations sche
 duled throughout the day. St Thomas Church will have a guide. Leviathan and
  Otter crews will encamp at Bonner’s Point. Children’s games. Talk and book
  signing by Dr. Benjamin Schaeffer on his book: First Fleets: Colonial Navi
 es of the British Atlantic. Food trucks.
DTEND:20260725T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260725T140000Z
GEO:35.476994;-76.811651
LOCATION:Historic Bath
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Patriots at Sea: An American Seaport Prepares for War
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52258839949760
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/patriots-at-sea-an-american-seaport-pr
 epares-for-war
END:VEVENT
