BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings,Outdoor & Recreation,Ou
 tdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes)
DESCRIPTION:Registration Required at Go Outdoors website: North Carolina WR
 C License - View Event. Participants must take Learn to Fly-fish: Basic Fly
 -casting before attending this program. This workshop is open to those 16 y
 ears and older. All minors must be accompanied by an adult.\n\nCurious abou
 t fly-fishing for bass\, panfish\, and other warmwater species? This hands-
 on introductory workshop breaks down the essentials\, from gear setup and f
 ly selection to understanding common warmwater fish. You’ll wrap up the exp
 erience by putting your new skills to use during a guided fishing session\,
  making this a perfect starting point for anyone ready to get on the water 
 with a fly rod.
DTEND:20260726T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030932Z
DTSTART:20260726T120000Z
GEO:36.250909;-79.756467
LOCATION:Haw River State Park\, Main Lodge at 339 Conference Center Drive\,
  Browns Summit\, NC 27214
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Learn to Fly-Fish NC: Intro to Warmwater Fly-Fishing
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51943241662294
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/learn-to-fly-fish-nc-intro-to-warmwate
 r-fly-fishing
