BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Exhibits & Tours,Special Site Programs,Outdoo
 r & Recreation,Nature & Wildlife Programs
DESCRIPTION:Calling all future Dune Rangers!  Join Ranger Austin and friend
 s for a fun\, educational\, and adventurous three-day camp.  Explore mariti
 me forests\, paddle on the Roanoke Sound\, climb the tallest active dune on
  the east coast\, be creative with cool arts and crafts projects\, play goo
 fy games\, help with stewardship projects\, and make new friends.  At the e
 nd of the week\, you will be an official Dune Ranger!  Our camp is supporte
 d by Friends of Jockey’s Ridge.  No cost to attend!\n\nJuly 29-July 31\, 20
 26     9:00am to 12:00pm daily\n\nOpen to grades 3-6.\n\nPre-registration i
 s required.  Please email austin.paul@ncparks.gov to signup.  \n\nThe missi
 on of the Dune Ranger Discovery Camp will focus on the following elements.\
 n\nProvide educational opportunities for our youth (both local and visitors
 )\,\n\nto promote stewardship and an appreciation for our natural areas\,\n
 \nto provide a safe place for our youth to interact with others and create 
 friendships\,\n\nto promote an active lifestyle\,\n\nallow for creativity\,
 \n\nand to have fun.
DTEND:20260729T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260729T130000Z
GEO:35.963597;-75.632255
LOCATION:Jockey's Ridge State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Dune Ranger Discovery Camp 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52011382804203
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/dune-ranger-discovery-camp-8318
END:VEVENT
