BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks,Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor
  Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:In honor of World Ranger Day\, join a ranger at Boone Fork Park
 ing Area (milepost 299.9 on the Blue Ridge Parkway) for a short stroll alon
 g the Tanawha Trail. Learn what rangers do on a day-to-day basis\, how we g
 ot our job\, and feel free to ask us questions! This short\, 1/4 mile easy 
 hike ends at a beautiful bridge over the Boone Fork Creek. Feel free to con
 tinue your hike onto Grandfather Mountain State Park trails from here\, or 
 turn around and walk back with the Ranger. \n\nPlease wear appropriate hiki
 ng shoes and dress for the weather.\n\nThere are no bathrooms at Boone Fork
  Parking Area.
DTEND:20260731T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260731T170000Z
LOCATION:Boone Fork Parking Area
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ranger Walk & Talk
