CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Learn about one of the small arms (musket\, flintlock\, or rifl
 e) that a soldier stationed at Fort Macon would have carried and used.\n\nT
 his will include a blank firing demonstration of the weapon.\nMeet in the f
 ort parade ground.\n\n \n\nPhoto by Jairus Hill : Living historian demonstr
 ating a musket at Fort Macon State Park.
DTEND:20260815T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260815T143000Z
GEO:34.696366;-76.684506
LOCATION:Fort Macon State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Small Arms Demonstration 10:30am & 2:30pm
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52019009728034
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/small-arms-demonstration-1030am-230pm
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Guided Tours
DESCRIPTION:Step into Tryon Palace and explore Diana Gabaldon’s award-winni
 ng Outlander series. Learn about the lives of the fictional Jamie and Clair
 e Fraser\, their family and friends\, and interactions with historical figu
 res and events in the tumultuous period of the American Revolution.\n\nTour
  covers storylines from Outlander books 4 – 8 and the Starz Outlander seaso
 ns 4 – 8. (For those not current on the books or show\, there will be spoil
 ers for these books and seasons.)\n\nTour begins at 301 George Street\, acr
 oss from the Tryon Palace Main Gates. Ticket holders should check in at the
  Waystation ticketing desk no later than 3:30 p.m.
DTEND:20260815T204500Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260815T194500Z
GEO:35.104831;-77.043044
LOCATION:Tryon Palace Historic Sites and Gardens
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Discover Tryon Palace: Outlander
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51931164601101
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/discover-tryon-palace-outlander
END:VEVENT
