BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History,Exhi
 bits & Tours,Special Site Programs
DESCRIPTION:Come down to Fort Macon and learn how the different cannons of 
 the fort were loaded\, aimed\, and shot.\n\nCannon firing demonstrations wi
 ll be held at 10:30 a.m.\; 11:30 a.m.\; 1:30 p.m.\; 2:30 p.m.\; and 3:30 p.
 m.\n\n \n\nPhoto by J. Hill: 10-inch mortar demonstration during Labor Day 
 Weekend Cannon Day at Ft. Macon State Park.
DTEND:20260905T193000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260905T143000Z
GEO:34.696366;-76.684506
LOCATION:Fort Macon State Park\, Ft. Macon
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ft. Macon Cannon Day
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51931025513881
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ft-macon-cannon-day
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Learn about one of the small arms (musket\, flintlock\, or rifl
 e) that a soldier stationed at Fort Macon would have carried and used.\n\nT
 his will include a blank firing demonstration of the weapon.\nMeet in the f
 ort parade ground.\n\n \n\nPhoto by Jairus Hill : Living historian demonstr
 ating a musket at Fort Macon State Park.
DTEND:20260905T183000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030933Z
DTSTART:20260905T143000Z
GEO:34.696366;-76.684506
