BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Indigenous Workshop - America 250 NC\,  introduces beginner
 s to the key steps and records that can unlock the  history of Black Indian
 s. Whether you’ve never started your search or you’ve hit a roadblock\, you
 ’ll learn how to make progress with confidence.\n\nIn this Native American 
 History Month presentation\, you’ll learn how to:\n\nBegin your family hist
 ory journey using records that are free and easy to access online.Find ance
 stors’ Tribal Rolls and Native American Records — and understand what those
  records reveal.Use clues from 1870 and beyond to trace family lines furthe
 r back in time.Overcome challenges created by the Trails of Tears\, Slavery
 \,  and Segregation-era record keeping.You’ll see how ordinary documents — 
 from Rolls and Census lists to Freedmen’s Bureau papers —   can tell extrao
 rdinary family stories.\n\nDeLoatch shares practical examples from his own 
 research\, showing how he traced his ancestry from Africa back 400 years to
  relatives enslaved in America.   Sponsored by the AFRO-AMERICAN HISTORICAL
  & GENEALOGICAL SOCIETY\, INC (AAHGS\, Inc.)\, North Carolina/Piedmont-Tria
 d Chapter
DTEND:20261114T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030934Z
DTSTART:20261114T150000Z
GEO:36.075685;-79.787776
LOCATION:Greensboro History Museum\, Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:BLACK INDIANS: "Native American Family Research"
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51619879291363
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/black-indians-native-american-family-r
 esearch
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:This season\, Hickory Ridge History Museum proudly reintroduces
  Living History Museum Days\, a return to the immersive\, hands-on spirit t
 hat once defined us as Hickory Ridge Living History Museum and “village”. O
 n select days this summer\, every cabin will come alive with the sights\, s
 ounds\, and smells of 18th-century life in the North Carolina mountains.\n\
 nFrom open-hearth cooking and blacksmithing to weaving\, spinning\, woodwor
 king\, and frontier chores\, guests will experience a day in the life of th
 e early settlers who called this region home. Our interpreters and voluntee
 rs will demonstrate traditional skills throughout the village\, inviting yo
 u to explore\, ask questions\, and connect with the everyday stories of App
 alachian history.
DTEND:20261114T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030934Z
DTSTART:20261114T150000Z
GEO:36.208683;-81.669982
LOCATION:Hickory Ridge History Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Living History Museum Days
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52506272795321
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/living-history-museum-days
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:We're going back to our roots.\n\nThis season\, Hickory Ridge H
 istory Museum proudly reintroduces Living History Museum Days\, a return to
  the immersive\, hands-on spirit that once defined us as Hickory Ridge Livi
 ng History Museum and “village”. On select days this summer\, the cabins wi
 ll come alive with the sights\, sounds\, and smells of 18th-century life in
  the North Carolina mountains.\n\nFrom open-hearth cooking and blacksmithin
 g to weaving\, spinning\, woodworking\, and frontier chores\, guests will e
 xperience a day in the life of the early settlers who called this region ho
 me. Our interpreters and volunteers will demonstrate traditional skills thr
 oughout the village\, inviting you to explore\, ask questions\, and connect
  with the everyday stories of Appalachian history.\n\nWhether you’re a long
 time visitor or discovering us for the first time\, Living History Museum D
 ays are your chance to step deeper into the past and to be part of its futu
 re.\n\nInterested in volunteering or learning an 18th-century skill? We’re 
 always looking for new hands to help bring the holler to life. Reach out to
  learn more about becoming part of SAHA family!
DTEND:20261114T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030934Z
DTSTART:20261114T150000Z
GEO:36.208683;-81.669982
LOCATION:Hickory Ridge History Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Living History Museum Days at Hickory Ridge History Museum in Boone
 \, NC
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52543890013505
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/living-history-museum-days-at-hickory-
 ridge-history-museum-in-boone-nc
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:Hidden Battleship is for the explorer at heart! Join us for an 
 afternoon on a unique\, behind-the-scenes tour of unrestored areas on the B
 attleship. Organized into small groups\, the participants are led to areas 
 in the bow\, third deck\, and below\, and the superstructure\, including al
 l the way to the very top! This program requires climbing ladders\, crossin
 g high hatches\, and going through tight/confined spaces. The tour is limit
 ed to ages 16 and older.\n\n2026 Dates\n\n► January 24\n► February 28\n► Ma
 rch 28\n► April 18\n► November 14\n\n11 am – 5 pm\; $75 (plus tax) per part
 icipant. This program always sells out\, so get your Hidden Battleship tick
 et now! This program is for ages 16 and older.
