URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/national-wreaths-across-america-day
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History,Exhi
 bits & Tours,Open Houses,Special Site Programs
DESCRIPTION:We cordially invite you to see Aycock Birthplace in a new light
 . Tour our historic buildings with costumed interpreters by candlelight and
  watch the preparation of a Christmas meal on a hearth all while learning a
 bout historical Christmas and New Years traditions. Admission is $5.00 (plu
 s tax)\, admission is free for visitors aged 12 and under.\nMore informatio
 n and details to be announced as the event approaches.
DTEND:20261220T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260410T030935Z
DTSTART:20261219T220000Z
GEO:35.520185;-77.976051
LOCATION:Governor Charles B. Aycock Birthplace
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Christmas Candlelight Open House
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207273191307
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/christmas-candlelight-open-house-2836
END:VEVENT
